WEBVTT

00:13.100 --> 00:15.189
[ominous music playing]

00:42.868 --> 00:45.436
[wind whistling]

00:48.961 --> 00:50.659
[owl hooting]

00:50.833 --> 00:52.269
[podcaster 1] What do you even
have to back it up?

00:52.443 --> 00:54.532
[podcaster 2]
There were eyewitnesses.

00:54.706 --> 00:58.188
A man fitting
Macher’s description
was spotted at a sorority party

00:58.362 --> 01:00.277
at Windsor College in 1997.

01:00.451 --> 01:02.236
The same year
the murders took place.

01:02.410 --> 01:03.976
[podcaster 1 scoffs]
It’s complete speculation,

01:04.151 --> 01:05.326
all right?
That’s never been confirmed.

01:05.500 --> 01:06.675
[podcaster 2]
It has been con--

01:10.809 --> 01:11.984
[sighs]

01:12.159 --> 01:13.943
Holy shit.

01:14.117 --> 01:15.640
[passenger] Ugh,
that was a long drive.

01:15.814 --> 01:17.381
[driver chuckles]

01:19.992 --> 01:22.125
Holy fucking shit!

01:22.299 --> 01:24.040
Can you get
a photo of me?

01:24.214 --> 01:25.389
Yeah.

01:28.262 --> 01:30.133
All right. Cute.

01:30.307 --> 01:31.134
[shutter clicking]

01:31.308 --> 01:32.092
[shouts]

01:32.266 --> 01:33.310
[passenger chuckles]

01:33.484 --> 01:35.791
I got it.
[chuckles]

01:36.879 --> 01:38.098
Wait, one more.
One more.

01:38.707 --> 01:39.751
[groans]

01:42.319 --> 01:44.626
Okay, I have to pee.
Let’s go inside.

01:44.800 --> 01:48.325
The code is...
[sighs, groans]

01:49.544 --> 01:53.939
...7-8-2-2.

01:54.114 --> 01:55.550
[lock clicks]

01:56.028 --> 01:57.421
[chuckles]

01:59.293 --> 02:02.426
Are you ready for...
[lock clicking]

02:04.298 --> 02:07.823
...the Macher House Experience?

02:07.997 --> 02:09.041
Wow.

02:09.999 --> 02:11.783
Oh.
[switch clicks]

02:13.133 --> 02:15.396
Oh, my God.
Ugh.

02:15.570 --> 02:17.572
Incredible.
Whoa.

02:17.746 --> 02:18.660
[driver chuckles]

02:18.834 --> 02:21.053
A real-life murder house.

02:21.228 --> 02:22.751
It’s perfect.
[sighs]

02:23.491 --> 02:24.796
Mm-hmm.
Right?

02:25.841 --> 02:27.495
I mean, it’s like--
it’s identical.

02:29.975 --> 02:31.063
Oh, this is cool.

02:31.238 --> 02:33.022
- The fake blood.
- Mm-hmm.

02:33.718 --> 02:34.850
Oh! [driver laughs]

02:35.024 --> 02:36.417
Check it out. Check it out.

02:36.591 --> 02:37.592
[groans]

02:37.766 --> 02:39.202
Ugh, I’m gonna pee my pants.

02:39.376 --> 02:40.812
[imitates gagging]
[shutter clicks]

02:40.986 --> 02:43.032
Babe, this is
where Sidney Prescott

02:43.206 --> 02:45.121
shot Billy Loomis in the face
right after she--

02:45.295 --> 02:47.515
Stabbed him with
the umbrella. I know.

02:47.689 --> 02:49.125
Where’s the bathroom?

02:49.299 --> 02:50.648
Oh, no, that’s the closet
Sidney was hiding in.

02:50.822 --> 02:52.694
Remember? Before she stabbed
him with the umbrella?

02:52.868 --> 02:53.956
Duh.

02:55.740 --> 02:57.177
[sighs]

02:59.657 --> 03:00.919
Oh, I found it!

03:01.093 --> 03:02.573
Oh. [chuckles]

03:03.183 --> 03:04.619
So cool.

03:09.058 --> 03:10.364
Ah.

03:10.538 --> 03:12.757
This is so cool!

03:13.932 --> 03:15.369
Incredible.

03:17.588 --> 03:18.850
Amber.

03:19.024 --> 03:20.852
And Richie. I mean...

03:23.072 --> 03:24.116
[shutter clicks]

03:25.292 --> 03:26.206
Ooh.

03:26.380 --> 03:27.772
[footsteps receding]

03:37.217 --> 03:38.305
Scott?

03:39.784 --> 03:41.612
[ominous music plays]

03:44.702 --> 03:46.095
Scott?

03:48.053 --> 03:49.490
Hello?

03:56.714 --> 03:58.238
Scott!

04:01.110 --> 04:02.677
Dude, where’d you go?

04:13.557 --> 04:14.558
[metal clinking]

04:15.733 --> 04:17.126
[screams]

04:18.606 --> 04:19.868
[breathing heavily]

04:21.043 --> 04:22.740
[both scream]

04:22.914 --> 04:24.612
Whoa. What’s wrong?
Oh, my God!
Ghostface is in there!

04:24.786 --> 04:25.656
What?

04:25.830 --> 04:26.701
Ghostface is in there!

04:26.875 --> 04:27.745
Someone with a ghost mask on.

04:27.919 --> 04:29.138
What are you talking about?

04:29.312 --> 04:30.270
There’s somebody in that room

04:30.444 --> 04:31.662
with a Ghostface mask on.

04:31.836 --> 04:33.098
Oh...

04:33.273 --> 04:34.665
[breathes shakily]
Do not go in there.

04:34.839 --> 04:36.624
Scott. Scott!

04:42.456 --> 04:44.458
[ominous music plays]

04:49.245 --> 04:50.725
[gasps]
Ooh!

04:50.899 --> 04:52.466
You’re going
to die tonight!
[chuckles]

04:55.469 --> 04:56.470
It’s fake.

05:00.648 --> 05:03.477
Oh, that is so cool.

05:03.651 --> 05:05.653
It’s got a motion sensor.

05:05.827 --> 05:07.481
Look at this.

05:07.655 --> 05:09.831
Do you like scary movies?

05:10.005 --> 05:12.181
[Scott]
I mean, come on, look at that.

05:12.355 --> 05:14.966
[sensor whirring]
That’s so cool.

05:15.750 --> 05:16.751
Pretty hi-tech.

05:17.491 --> 05:18.883
It looked so real.

05:19.057 --> 05:21.843
That is sweet!

05:22.670 --> 05:23.932
Wow.

05:24.106 --> 05:27.501
It’s plugged in
right here.
What?

05:27.675 --> 05:30.286
Ah, so this is it.
This is so creepy.

05:30.460 --> 05:32.244
The room where
Stu held that party

05:32.419 --> 05:34.246
to lure Sidney Prescott
to her death.

05:34.421 --> 05:36.771
You know, they say Billy
was the mastermind,

05:36.945 --> 05:39.817
but I’ve always been
more of a Stu-head.

05:39.991 --> 05:40.992
Who was your favorite?
What?

05:41.166 --> 05:43.299
My favorite
homicidal teenager?

05:43.473 --> 05:44.561
Neither.

05:45.649 --> 05:46.911
Are you gonna be like this
the whole time?

05:47.085 --> 05:48.391
What do you want me to do?

05:49.000 --> 05:50.132
[mutters] Um...

05:50.306 --> 05:52.047
Okay. Babe,
did you know that this is

05:52.221 --> 05:54.049
where Sidney dropped a TV
on Stu’s head?

05:54.223 --> 05:56.094
Squished all the crazy
out of his brain?

05:56.268 --> 05:59.141
Ah, but did she kill him?

05:59.315 --> 06:02.492
You heard the podcast.
There’s a lot of theories
out there that Stu survived.

06:02.666 --> 06:04.059
[passenger] No.
There was a dead body.

06:04.233 --> 06:06.757
It was taken to the morgue
and then buried.

06:06.931 --> 06:09.064
[hums]
You can’t fake that.

06:09.238 --> 06:10.892
Let’s check out the kitchen.

06:19.466 --> 06:21.337
Ooh.

06:21.511 --> 06:23.426
Oh, this is where Sidney
and Gale Weathers

06:23.600 --> 06:25.515
roasted Amber Freeman
a few years ago.

06:25.689 --> 06:28.039
Yeah, where
she was torched. [sighs]

06:28.213 --> 06:30.215
I would hate to die that way.

06:38.659 --> 06:39.573
[gasps]

06:39.747 --> 06:41.009
Oh, my God.
It’s fake.

06:41.183 --> 06:42.271
It’s fake. [chuckles]

06:42.445 --> 06:43.881
Fucking hilarious.

06:44.534 --> 06:45.927
[phone rings]

06:47.015 --> 06:48.669
It’s happening.

06:50.235 --> 06:52.281
[line beeps]
Hello?

06:52.455 --> 06:54.936
[voice on phone]
Hello, Scott. Hello, Madison.

06:55.110 --> 06:57.155
Welcome to
the Macher House Experience.

06:57.329 --> 06:58.896
Enjoying it so far?

06:59.070 --> 07:00.245
It’s amazing.
Mm-hmm.

07:00.420 --> 07:02.552
Do you like scary movies?

07:02.726 --> 07:04.119
Go, go.

07:04.293 --> 07:06.382
Uh, yeah, my boyfriend’s
a big horror fan.

07:06.556 --> 07:08.384
What’s your favorite
scary movie?

07:08.558 --> 07:10.865
Stab One.
It’s time to play a game.

07:11.039 --> 07:13.389
Scary Movie Trivia.
Three questions.

07:13.563 --> 07:16.610
Get one wrong, and you die.
Question one:

07:16.784 --> 07:19.177
In the original
A Nightmare on Elm Street,

07:19.351 --> 07:21.528
who is the first person
to die?

07:21.702 --> 07:23.225
Tina Gray.
Correct.

07:23.399 --> 07:24.705
Question two:

07:24.879 --> 07:26.576
InThe People
Under the Stairs,

07:26.750 --> 07:28.970
what’s the name of
Mommy and Daddy’s daughter?

07:29.144 --> 07:30.754
Alice.
Very good.

07:30.928 --> 07:32.713
Let’s try a hard one
this time.

07:32.887 --> 07:34.105
InFriday the 13th,

07:34.279 --> 07:37.326
how old was Jason Voorhees
when he drowned?

07:38.327 --> 07:40.460
Okay, well,
in The Final Chapter

07:40.634 --> 07:44.507
we found out Mrs. Voorhees
gave birth in 1946, right?

07:44.681 --> 07:48.337
And then in the original,
the two counselors died
in the flashback in ’58.

07:48.511 --> 07:50.992
Jason drowned the summer
before that. That’s ’57.

07:51.166 --> 07:54.474
So born in ’46,
drowned in ’57.

07:55.213 --> 07:57.172
Eleven. Jason was eleven.

07:57.346 --> 08:01.350
Oh, I’m so sorry, Scott,
but that’s incorrect.

08:02.438 --> 08:04.962
Bullshit.
No, the math was right.

08:05.136 --> 08:07.661
It’s a trick question.
Jason never drowned.

08:07.835 --> 08:09.837
Very impressive, Madison.

08:10.011 --> 08:12.361
Scott’s lucky he has you
to lean on.

08:12.535 --> 08:16.321
I guess I don’t get to stab
you guys after all.[chuckles]

08:16.496 --> 08:17.801
You two have a chilling night.

08:17.975 --> 08:20.195
And don’t forget to give us
a five-star--

08:21.326 --> 08:22.327
Are you miserable?

08:22.502 --> 08:24.025
I wish I could fake it better.

08:24.199 --> 08:25.330
Why’d you come here
with me?

08:25.505 --> 08:27.550
Well, you were
pushy about it!

08:27.724 --> 08:32.033
And I thought I could be cool,
then we got here
and it’s so cheesy.

08:32.207 --> 08:33.513
You want to go?

08:33.687 --> 08:34.775
I don’t want to be here
if you don’t.

08:34.949 --> 08:36.211
I can drive home right now.

08:36.385 --> 08:37.255
You would drive home
right now?

08:37.429 --> 08:38.561
I would.

08:39.127 --> 08:41.172
No, it’s too late.

08:42.304 --> 08:43.435
I’m sorry.

08:43.610 --> 08:45.960
I’m gonna try harder.
I promise.

08:50.051 --> 08:51.922
Okay, now I have to pee.

08:52.096 --> 08:53.576
It’s the hallway
on the left.
[chuckles]

08:57.493 --> 08:59.626
[exhales, smacks lips]

08:59.800 --> 09:01.105
[sighs]

09:01.845 --> 09:03.107
[phone rings]

09:08.765 --> 09:10.114
Hello?

09:10.288 --> 09:12.726
[caller] You’re going to
die tonight.

09:13.901 --> 09:15.555
Scott, why are you calling me?

09:15.729 --> 09:17.731
[caller] It’s not Scott.

09:18.645 --> 09:20.168
Okay.

09:21.299 --> 09:22.692
Who is it then?

09:22.866 --> 09:25.608
[caller] The person
who’s gonna kill you.

09:25.782 --> 09:28.306
The scary voice thing is
a little bit sexy,

09:28.480 --> 09:29.917
but you could work on it.

09:30.091 --> 09:31.788
[caller]
Listen, you little bitch,

09:31.962 --> 09:34.748
I’m gonna slice you open
and rip your guts out!

09:34.922 --> 09:37.228
Did you just call me a bitch?

09:37.402 --> 09:40.536
Okay, I said I would try,
but I’m done. This isn’t fun.

09:40.710 --> 09:43.670
[caller] Because the fun part
is over, Madison.

09:43.844 --> 09:45.019
[line beeps]

09:45.802 --> 09:46.934
[object thuds]

09:52.026 --> 09:53.288
Scott?

09:55.377 --> 09:57.945
They’d never make it
in time.

10:08.608 --> 10:09.609
Scott!

10:09.783 --> 10:12.307
We’re not finished yet.

10:23.710 --> 10:25.059
Fuck you!

10:25.537 --> 10:26.451
Stu--

10:26.626 --> 10:28.671
[gasps, screams]

10:29.324 --> 10:31.413
[Scott groans] Ow! Ow!

10:31.587 --> 10:34.372
It’s me.
What the fuck?

10:34.546 --> 10:36.636
[groans] You hit me.
What is wrong with you?

10:36.810 --> 10:38.115
I’m sorry. I thought it...

10:38.289 --> 10:39.856
[panting]
[gasps]

10:40.030 --> 10:41.771
You said you were gonna try.
[stutters] It was a bad idea.

10:41.945 --> 10:44.644
Yeah, of course it was
a bad fucking idea!

10:46.733 --> 10:48.169
It moved.

10:48.343 --> 10:49.823
Yeah, it’s electric.
That’s what it does.

10:49.997 --> 10:52.826
No. Like, it moved

10:53.522 --> 10:54.871
differently.

10:56.090 --> 10:57.657
[Madison] What?

10:57.831 --> 10:59.833
Oh!
[Madison screams]

11:00.007 --> 11:01.922
[Scott grunts, groans]

11:04.054 --> 11:05.403
[gasps] No!

11:05.577 --> 11:08.363
[screams, sobs]

11:12.367 --> 11:13.977
[screams]

11:18.547 --> 11:19.591
[panting]

11:22.290 --> 11:24.074
[screaming]

11:27.469 --> 11:28.731
[panting]

11:30.820 --> 11:31.821
[screams]

11:39.394 --> 11:41.048
Fuck you! [screams]

11:41.701 --> 11:43.137
[grunts]

11:44.094 --> 11:45.835
[dramatic music playing]

11:58.326 --> 11:59.936
[screams]

12:01.503 --> 12:03.461
[grunting, breathing heavily]

12:10.251 --> 12:11.818
[screams, pants]

12:19.086 --> 12:21.566
[screams]

12:21.741 --> 12:22.829
[flesh squelches]

12:25.092 --> 12:27.007
[grunting, panting]

12:29.270 --> 12:30.837
[groans]

12:31.011 --> 12:32.490
[quiet, high-pitched ringing]

12:41.282 --> 12:42.500
[clattering]

12:52.032 --> 12:53.642
[muttering weakly]

12:56.776 --> 12:58.168
[flames roar]

13:02.564 --> 13:04.653
[whimpering, groaning]

13:04.827 --> 13:08.788
No! No, no, no. No, no, no.
[cries]

13:09.440 --> 13:10.659
[sobbing]

13:11.660 --> 13:14.358
[screaming]

13:20.364 --> 13:21.583
[glass shatters]

13:22.714 --> 13:24.804
[dramatic music playing]

13:41.516 --> 13:43.300
[phone ringing]

13:45.433 --> 13:46.913
[screaming]

13:48.175 --> 13:50.177
["Criminal" playing]

13:53.223 --> 13:54.834
[typing]

13:57.140 --> 13:58.794
[phone chimes]

14:07.890 --> 14:09.022
[crunching]

14:10.675 --> 14:12.808
[ominous music plays]

14:24.951 --> 14:25.995
[screams]

14:26.169 --> 14:27.518
Jesus, you scared me.

14:27.692 --> 14:29.564
You’re gonna give me
a heart attack.

14:29.738 --> 14:32.219
I’m sorry.
What are you doing here?

14:32.915 --> 14:33.916
Well...

14:36.658 --> 14:39.661
it occurred to me
that I’ve never snuck through
your bedroom window.

14:40.401 --> 14:42.577
I was home, bored,

14:43.970 --> 14:44.884
watching TV...

14:45.058 --> 14:46.059
Mmm.

14:49.453 --> 14:51.107
...and Stabwas on.

14:52.065 --> 14:53.762
And that just got me
thinking of you.

14:53.936 --> 14:55.459
That’s horrific.

14:55.633 --> 14:57.331
Billy snuck through
Sidney’s window, so...

14:57.505 --> 14:59.942
Mm-hmm.
I’m well aware.

15:00.116 --> 15:02.162
You know,
if my mom catches you...

15:02.336 --> 15:04.729
Mmm. Just a kiss.

15:14.826 --> 15:15.740
Hey.

15:15.915 --> 15:17.046
Hi.

15:23.531 --> 15:24.445
[knocking on door]
[boyfriend] Oh!

15:24.619 --> 15:26.055
[body thuds]

15:26.229 --> 15:27.448
[door opens]

15:28.188 --> 15:29.580
Can you knock?

15:29.754 --> 15:31.234
I did.

15:31.408 --> 15:32.627
Can you wait for a response?

15:33.323 --> 15:34.324
Something wrong?

15:34.890 --> 15:36.152
No.

15:36.326 --> 15:37.762
No, everything’s fine.
You sure?

15:37.937 --> 15:38.807
Mm-hmm.

15:38.981 --> 15:40.809
Ben, how you doing over there?

15:40.983 --> 15:44.160
On the floor. Behind the bed.

15:44.900 --> 15:47.685
Hello, Mrs. Evans.

15:47.859 --> 15:49.209
How are you this evening?

15:49.383 --> 15:52.299
Oh, well, I’m tired.
Ben, it’s late.

15:52.473 --> 15:55.476
That’s why I didn’t want to
disturb anyone by...

15:55.650 --> 15:56.956
using the door.

15:57.130 --> 15:58.609
So thoughtful.

15:59.697 --> 16:00.655
Out.

16:00.829 --> 16:02.265
But he’s here now.
No.

16:02.439 --> 16:04.093
That’s okay. I’m going.

16:08.880 --> 16:10.534
Good night, Tate.

16:15.757 --> 16:18.716
[Ben] I know it’s late.
I’m sorry, Mrs. Evans.

16:18.890 --> 16:21.806
That was on me.
Tatum had no idea
that I was coming over.

16:21.981 --> 16:24.984
Okay, well,
let’s not do it again.

16:27.551 --> 16:28.639
[sighs]

16:32.208 --> 16:33.601
I’m a good guy, Mrs. Evans.

16:33.775 --> 16:35.037
Good night, Ben.

16:46.092 --> 16:47.397
Hypocrite.

16:50.313 --> 16:51.662
[scoffs]

16:55.144 --> 16:57.755
It’s not like a boy’s never
crawled through your window.

16:57.929 --> 16:59.844
[phone chimes]
We’ve all seen the movie.

17:00.019 --> 17:02.369
Which is why it’s never
gonna happen in this house.

17:02.543 --> 17:04.327
Why do you not like him?

17:05.241 --> 17:06.460
[sighs]

17:06.634 --> 17:07.852
I don’t not like him.

17:08.027 --> 17:09.724
I just--
I want you to be smart.

17:09.898 --> 17:11.726
And not trust him so easily.

17:11.900 --> 17:13.206
We’re not having sex,

17:13.380 --> 17:14.903
if that’s
what you’re worried about.

17:15.512 --> 17:17.036
I mean, we want to,

17:18.298 --> 17:20.082
but I don’t think we’re ready.

17:20.256 --> 17:23.129
Well, if you’re asking
the question, then, um...

17:23.912 --> 17:25.479
you’re probably not.

17:25.653 --> 17:27.002
How did you know?

17:30.745 --> 17:33.226
I mean,
did that really happen to you?

17:33.400 --> 17:34.401
Like in the movie?

17:37.491 --> 17:39.232
It’s freezing in here.

17:40.320 --> 17:41.582
[Sidney exhales]

17:45.847 --> 17:47.327
How about we have
these kinds of conversations

17:47.501 --> 17:49.416
during waking hours, okay?

17:49.590 --> 17:52.767
No more boys in windows, please.

17:53.768 --> 17:54.812
[Sidney sighs]

17:56.553 --> 17:57.685
Night.

17:59.600 --> 18:01.689
[sighs]

18:07.782 --> 18:09.044
How ugly did it get?

18:10.959 --> 18:12.482
I was extremely polite.

18:12.656 --> 18:14.397
You know,
she’s not the first girl

18:14.571 --> 18:16.007
to let a boy
sneak in her window.

18:16.182 --> 18:18.401
Yeah. She made that point.

18:18.575 --> 18:20.316
You know, if being
an overprotective mom

18:20.490 --> 18:22.492
is the worst thing she can
say about me... [sighs]

18:22.666 --> 18:24.277
...I think I can
live with that.

18:24.451 --> 18:25.626
You think they’re doing it?

18:25.800 --> 18:28.150
Oh, God, no.

18:28.324 --> 18:30.979
[chuckles] No. Not yet.

18:31.153 --> 18:33.242
But I think we’ve got
about five minutes left.

18:34.809 --> 18:36.811
How old were you
when you started?

18:36.985 --> 18:38.987
Same age as you. Seventeen.

18:39.161 --> 18:42.033
Oh, did I say seventeen?
I think I meant fifteen.

18:43.774 --> 18:44.993
Did you lie to me?

18:45.167 --> 18:47.996
Look, in my defense,
I don’t remember.

18:48.170 --> 18:50.346
Oh, you don’t remember
the first time you had sex?

18:50.520 --> 18:52.348
Oh, no, I don’t remember
what I told you.

18:52.522 --> 18:54.611
Oh, you told me seventeen.

18:54.785 --> 18:57.658
Look, I didn’t want to
come off as, you know...

18:57.832 --> 18:59.573
Uh-huh. Keep going.
I want to see where this goes.

18:59.747 --> 19:01.749
[stammers] I just wanted you
to see me

19:01.923 --> 19:03.620
as more than a sex slave.

19:03.794 --> 19:06.797
Oh. You have a mind, too?

19:06.971 --> 19:08.886
You know... well, yeah.

19:09.060 --> 19:11.106
[gentle music playing]

19:20.028 --> 19:22.073
[people chuckling]

19:22.248 --> 19:24.511
[rock music playing]

19:24.685 --> 19:26.687
[saw whirring]

19:26.861 --> 19:28.079
[people chattering
indistinctly]

19:30.256 --> 19:31.648
[contractor] Morning, Chief.

19:31.822 --> 19:33.215
Hey, Woody. Look at that,
the walls are up, right?

19:33.389 --> 19:35.217
Looks great.

19:35.391 --> 19:37.350
[child on tablet] Love you.
I love you, too.
We miss you guys.

19:37.524 --> 19:39.352
[Mark]
Construction’s coming along.
We’re keeping them busy.

19:39.526 --> 19:41.441
Oh. Hey, Mom.
[mother] Hi there, baby.

19:41.615 --> 19:44.531
[child] Hi, Daddy.
Thanks, Junie.
I’m glad you’re having fun.

19:44.705 --> 19:46.402
If you need anything, call.
Okay.

19:46.576 --> 19:48.709
I love you. Thank you
for watching the maniacs.

19:48.883 --> 19:50.232
We’ll see you this weekend.

19:50.406 --> 19:51.190
Bye.
Bye.

19:51.364 --> 19:52.234
[tablet chimes]

19:52.408 --> 19:54.541
She’s very brave.
Yep.

19:57.718 --> 19:59.807
[ominous music plays]
[saw whirs]

20:01.678 --> 20:02.679
What?

20:03.680 --> 20:05.247
Where’d you find that?

20:05.421 --> 20:06.857
Um, the attic.

20:07.031 --> 20:08.511
I was looking through
some old clothes.

20:11.688 --> 20:13.255
Do you not want me to wear it?

20:13.429 --> 20:14.735
You could have asked.

20:17.520 --> 20:19.087
Honey, maybe take it off.

20:25.876 --> 20:27.748
What age
do they get nice again?

20:29.576 --> 20:30.925
That was on you.

20:32.927 --> 20:34.233
[inhales deeply]

20:34.842 --> 20:36.757
[sighs]

20:39.586 --> 20:41.109
[mysterious music plays]

20:42.197 --> 20:43.459
[sighs]

20:46.810 --> 20:48.508
You can wear the jacket.

20:49.422 --> 20:50.597
It’s okay, I’m good.

20:51.162 --> 20:52.947
Tatum, I’m sorry.

20:53.121 --> 20:54.427
Okay? It caught me off guard.

20:54.601 --> 20:55.993
I hadn’t seen it
since college.

20:56.167 --> 20:58.126
I thought I’d gotten rid
of it.

20:58.300 --> 21:00.911
Yeah, the mysterious
one semester at Windsor
we can’t talk about.

21:01.085 --> 21:02.086
That’s not true.

21:02.261 --> 21:04.611
Really? Since when?

21:04.785 --> 21:07.222
Your childhood is
completely off-limits.

21:07.396 --> 21:10.225
[laughs]
What are you talking about?
It’s not off-limits.

21:10.399 --> 21:12.140
It’s online and in movies
and in books.

21:12.314 --> 21:14.011
You could do a deep dive
whenever you want.

21:14.185 --> 21:15.796
As long as
I don’t ask questions.

21:19.626 --> 21:21.454
You have rehearsal today?

21:22.933 --> 21:23.978
Yep.

21:25.632 --> 21:26.981
How’s it going?

21:29.679 --> 21:30.637
Horrible.

21:31.377 --> 21:33.422
Tragic. [chuckles]

21:33.596 --> 21:36.077
I get so nervous onstage,
it’s painful to watch.

21:36.251 --> 21:39.559
Oh, God! I used to
get stage fright.
I know the feeling.

21:40.342 --> 21:42.083
You did theater?

21:44.085 --> 21:45.434
Not since college.

21:47.567 --> 21:50.874
Anyway, don’t worry.
You’re gonna do great.

21:52.833 --> 21:54.313
I got to get to work.

21:59.448 --> 22:00.971
Fucking motherhood.

22:01.145 --> 22:02.843
Great talk.

22:03.017 --> 22:05.019
["The Kill" playing]

22:30.261 --> 22:33.264
["The Kill" continues
through speakers]

22:35.310 --> 22:36.833
Morning.
Hey, morning.

22:42.839 --> 22:44.232
[server] We’ll have that
right out for you. Okay?

22:44.406 --> 22:45.799
[customer]
All right. Thank you.

22:45.973 --> 22:47.975
Busy?
Little AM rush,
but not too bad.

22:48.149 --> 22:49.237
Good. [sighs]

22:49.411 --> 22:51.718
Hey, Mrs. Evans.
Hey, Lucas.

22:51.892 --> 22:53.807
Oh, could I get
four espresso shots, please?

22:53.981 --> 22:54.895
Yeah. For sure.

22:55.069 --> 22:57.376
Four?
Yeah. [chuckles]

22:57.550 --> 22:59.682
Rehearsal today.
It’s gonna be a long one.

22:59.856 --> 23:01.249
What part do you play?

23:01.423 --> 23:02.511
Oh, just a techie. Yeah.

23:02.685 --> 23:05.166
I work the, uh--
the lighting board.

23:05.340 --> 23:07.255
- Cool.
- Yeah. [inhales sharply]

23:07.429 --> 23:08.735
Hey, an old Dateline
was on last night

23:08.909 --> 23:10.127
about the Ghostface Killers
in New York.

23:10.301 --> 23:11.477
Have you, uh--
Have you seen it?

23:11.651 --> 23:13.957
No, I haven’t.

23:14.131 --> 23:16.482
It’s not as good as the
Netflix doc, but it’s decent.

23:16.656 --> 23:18.397
They did a good job
covering the aftermath.

23:18.571 --> 23:20.094
[sighs] Morning.

23:20.268 --> 23:21.400
Hey.

23:21.574 --> 23:22.749
Did you say anything?
Mm-mmm.

23:22.923 --> 23:24.054
Did he ask you about Dateline?

23:24.228 --> 23:25.316
It’s fine, really.

23:25.491 --> 23:26.883
No, it isn’t.

23:27.057 --> 23:28.145
I told you not to.
Ow!

23:28.319 --> 23:30.017
That hurt.
Good.

23:30.191 --> 23:33.324
I’m a crime junkie, Mom.
It’s my-- It’s my thing.

23:33.499 --> 23:35.762
[sighs] I’m sorry, Mrs. Evans.

23:35.936 --> 23:37.938
But I really want to
start a podcast,

23:38.112 --> 23:39.026
and I think
the New York murders

23:39.200 --> 23:40.506
would be a primo first case.

23:40.680 --> 23:42.812
Don’t you have
rehearsal now, honey?

23:42.986 --> 23:44.205
Right?
Yes.

23:44.379 --> 23:46.512
So you should leave now.
Right. Yeah. Okay.

23:46.686 --> 23:47.948
Okay. Great.
Bye.

23:48.122 --> 23:49.297
- Bye.
- Bye!

23:49.471 --> 23:52.082
[sighs] I’m sorry.
It’s fine.

23:52.822 --> 23:54.041
What’ll you have?

23:54.215 --> 23:56.217
["The Kill" continues]

23:59.960 --> 24:01.701
["The Kill" continues
through earbuds]

24:01.875 --> 24:03.659
[Tatum] Hey, wait up!

24:03.833 --> 24:05.139
[friend] Oh, hey.
[friend 2] Hi!

24:05.313 --> 24:07.489
You look hot.
Where’d you get the jacket?

24:07.663 --> 24:09.709
Thanks. It’s my mom’s.
’90s vintage.

24:09.883 --> 24:11.014
[gasps]
You should bedazzle it.

24:11.188 --> 24:12.146
Yes.

24:12.320 --> 24:14.191
Oh! Tonight,
my place, party.

24:14.365 --> 24:15.802
I’ve been stockpiling
my mom’s edibles.

24:15.976 --> 24:17.891
And you can even
invite creepy boy.

24:18.065 --> 24:19.545
Listen, he’s not creepy.

24:19.719 --> 24:21.068
Mmm.
He’s deep.

24:21.242 --> 24:22.983
And he has a squeezy butt.
Ew.

24:23.157 --> 24:25.855
The true crime is cringy.
He’s obsessed with my mom.

24:26.029 --> 24:28.118
Is your mom gonna let you out
of your cage tonight?

24:28.292 --> 24:30.164
I-- [sighs] I don’t know.

24:30.338 --> 24:33.689
Honestly,
she’s been on overdrive
with the mama trauma.

24:33.863 --> 24:36.997
Well, if anyone has a right
to be insane, it is your mom.

24:37.171 --> 24:38.912
Very true. I’ve seen
all the Stabmovies.

24:39.086 --> 24:41.175
Personally, I don’t know how
she’s not in a psych ward.

24:41.349 --> 24:42.263
[horn honks]

24:42.437 --> 24:43.351
Oh.
Oh.

24:43.525 --> 24:45.396
Look who it is.
[Ben] Hey!

24:45.571 --> 24:49.009
Top of the morning!
Hey, Tay.

24:49.183 --> 24:50.097
- Hey, babe.
- Hiya.

24:50.271 --> 24:51.925
You all need a lift?

24:52.099 --> 24:54.188
You guys, come on!
Yes!

24:54.362 --> 24:57.017
We don’t have to walk anymore.
Let’s go!
Yeah, yeah, yeah. Buckle up.

24:57.191 --> 24:58.845
[pop punk music playing]

24:59.019 --> 25:00.803
Buckle up. Buckle up!

25:01.761 --> 25:03.240
[teenagers laugh]

25:03.806 --> 25:04.677
Karl!

25:14.164 --> 25:15.775
Thank you.

25:16.689 --> 25:19.126
I am so sorry about Lucas.
No.

25:19.300 --> 25:21.476
It’s just you’re like
a celebrity to him.

25:23.739 --> 25:25.828
You feel like
you guys are close, right?

25:26.002 --> 25:29.963
Yeah. I mean, I suppose
we’ve had to be
since it’s just the two of us.

25:30.137 --> 25:33.793
Do you ever talk to him about
your life before you had him?

25:33.967 --> 25:35.272
No.
No?

25:35.446 --> 25:37.361
No, no. I mean,
there’s not much I can say

25:37.536 --> 25:39.320
about his abusive
asshole father

25:39.494 --> 25:42.279
and how badly our marriage
fucked me up.

25:42.453 --> 25:44.238
Why? What’s going on?

25:44.412 --> 25:46.501
Oh, I don’t know. Uh...

25:46.675 --> 25:49.243
Tatum and I are having
a bit of a rough patch.

25:49.417 --> 25:52.333
She’s at that age where she
wants to know about my past.

25:52.507 --> 25:54.465
And as you know, my past
is full of dead people.

25:54.640 --> 25:57.512
Not exactly something
I want to share with her.

25:57.686 --> 26:00.341
So I get quiet,
and then she gets loud,

26:00.515 --> 26:02.299
and around and around we go.

26:02.473 --> 26:04.301
Listen. She’s your daughter,

26:04.475 --> 26:06.782
and it’s natural
she should want to know you.

26:06.956 --> 26:08.436
You know, I just--
I want my kids to be able

26:08.610 --> 26:11.004
to be who they are
without living in fear.

26:11.178 --> 26:13.615
I want them to feel safe
and protected.

26:13.789 --> 26:15.617
But it’s not
a safe world, Sid.

26:15.791 --> 26:17.532
And if we protect
our children too much,

26:17.706 --> 26:19.926
they’ll never learn
how to protect themselves.

26:22.972 --> 26:26.062
[performer]
♪ Be not afraid
Don’t run away ♪

26:26.236 --> 26:29.370
♪ In here you’re safe
Inside your dreamscape ♪

26:29.544 --> 26:31.851
♪ It’s meant to be
I come to thee ♪

26:32.025 --> 26:34.810
♪ So will you come with me?♪

26:34.984 --> 26:37.334
♪ I’ll show you
That you’re capable ♪

26:37.508 --> 26:41.208
♪ Of knowing things
You’ve never known ♪

26:41.382 --> 26:43.776
♪ I promise
Life is beautiful ♪

26:43.950 --> 26:45.734
[Tatum] Oh, fuck! [groans]

26:45.908 --> 26:47.301
[performer] ♪ Beautiful ♪

26:48.084 --> 26:49.172
Watch out!

26:49.782 --> 26:51.958
[screams] Oh, fuck!

26:52.828 --> 26:54.351
[chuckles]

26:54.525 --> 26:55.570
[techie] Sorry.

26:56.092 --> 26:57.006
Fuck me.

26:57.180 --> 26:58.442
I’m stuck!

26:58.617 --> 26:59.879
[teacher] No.

27:00.053 --> 27:03.186
No. Uh, houselights, please.

27:03.360 --> 27:04.710
Where’s Aaron? Aaron!

27:04.884 --> 27:06.015
I’m here!

27:06.189 --> 27:08.583
I panicked.
I saw Fluffy and freaked.

27:08.757 --> 27:10.324
Are you trying to kill me?
I’m sorry.

27:10.498 --> 27:12.805
[performer] Come, get me out.
Get me out of it.

27:12.979 --> 27:14.807
[groans] I can’t see anything
through this.

27:14.981 --> 27:15.982
Wardrobe! Chloe!

27:16.156 --> 27:17.461
Oh! Yep, I’m here.

27:17.636 --> 27:19.681
I’m over here.
I’m here, I’m here!

27:19.855 --> 27:22.641
My foot keeps on getting stuck
in this dumbass pouch
every time.

27:22.815 --> 27:24.207
Okay, diva. Calm down.

27:24.381 --> 27:25.339
Hey, I’m sorry, Hannah.

27:25.513 --> 27:27.297
Oh, no, you’re fine.

27:27.471 --> 27:30.083
Trust me, I’m not a real diva.
Just playing the part of one.

27:30.257 --> 27:32.563
But you don’t know that.
You stay scared.

27:33.260 --> 27:34.522
Scram!
[Aaron gasps]

27:34.696 --> 27:36.219
Hannah. Hannah, darling.

27:37.351 --> 27:38.352
[Hannah clears throat]

27:38.526 --> 27:40.746
You and Aaron
need to practice.

27:40.920 --> 27:43.618
Uh, Mr. Willis, I missed
my cue. It’s my fault.

27:43.792 --> 27:45.751
Tatum... a word.

27:49.189 --> 27:50.756
We need to talk about
your Fluffy.

27:50.930 --> 27:53.193
Yeah, I can’t see
through Fluffy’s eyes.

27:53.367 --> 27:55.891
It’s more than that.
You’re very lackluster.

27:56.587 --> 27:58.198
Fluffy needs energy.

27:58.372 --> 28:00.374
Dogs are lively creatures.

28:00.548 --> 28:03.159
You’re too timid. Tatum,
where’s your confidence?

28:03.333 --> 28:05.945
You need to bring
more strength to this role.

28:06.119 --> 28:07.642
I’ll work on that.

28:09.513 --> 28:11.341
You’re Sidney Prescott’s
daughter.

28:11.515 --> 28:14.605
You need to channel
some of your mother’s fire.

28:15.694 --> 28:17.173
I’m surprised really.

28:18.305 --> 28:20.046
I thought you had more grit.

28:22.352 --> 28:24.572
Well, that was rude.

28:24.746 --> 28:27.967
You’re playing a dog.
Your only line is "Woof."
It’s not that deep.

28:28.141 --> 28:30.143
Hey, fuck him.

28:30.317 --> 28:31.753
Yeah, fuck him.

28:31.927 --> 28:33.363
Ah, don’t let Willis
get to you.

28:33.537 --> 28:36.236
Your Fluffy’s incredible.
Thanks, guys.

28:36.410 --> 28:37.803
Um...

28:37.977 --> 28:39.674
Okay, I’m--
I’m gonna go take this off.

28:40.327 --> 28:42.198
I’ll help you.

28:42.372 --> 28:43.591
Uh, don’t forget.
Party tonight.

28:43.765 --> 28:45.158
My place.
All right.

28:45.332 --> 28:46.115
Whoo!
Mmm!

28:46.289 --> 28:47.813
[chuckles]

28:47.987 --> 28:49.771
[Tatum] Ugh.
Get me out of this thing.

28:49.945 --> 28:51.904
[Ben] I got it.
[zipper unzipping]

28:52.992 --> 28:54.297
That’s it.

28:54.471 --> 28:56.691
["Nothing’s Gonna
Hurt You Baby" playing]

28:57.387 --> 28:58.824
[sighs]

28:58.998 --> 29:00.695
Am I timid?

29:00.869 --> 29:02.566
Oh, don’t let that asshole
get to you.

29:02.741 --> 29:04.699
Answer the question.
Be honest.

29:05.700 --> 29:08.094
I wouldn’t say timid, no, but

29:08.268 --> 29:11.750
you have
this really cute shy quality.

29:14.013 --> 29:16.624
"Shy" means "timid," FYI.

29:20.497 --> 29:22.282
Do you think
I lack confidence?

29:22.456 --> 29:25.285
[chuckles] I can’t win this.
I’m not playing.

29:25.459 --> 29:26.547
[Tatum mutters, scoffs]

29:27.722 --> 29:30.551
Why do you like me?
That’s a really long list.

29:30.725 --> 29:33.554
Okay.
Well, be specific. One thing.

29:36.470 --> 29:39.299
[sighs] No.
It’s-- It’s cheesy.

29:43.216 --> 29:44.783
Say it anyway.

29:46.262 --> 29:47.916
Okay.

29:50.397 --> 29:53.313
I like how you look at me
in a certain way.

29:53.487 --> 29:54.705
And it makes me smile.

29:54.880 --> 29:57.665
Or you say something
that makes me laugh,

29:59.188 --> 30:00.711
and I’ll go home
and I’ll think about it later

30:00.886 --> 30:03.323
and I’ll smile
and laugh all over again.

30:05.325 --> 30:07.066
I really like that.

30:13.899 --> 30:16.858
That wasn’t cheesy.
That was a great answer.

30:17.032 --> 30:19.339
["Nothing’s Gonna
Hurt You Baby" continues]

30:27.564 --> 30:28.957
[phone rings]

30:32.352 --> 30:35.007
Hello.
[caller] Hello, Sidney.

30:35.181 --> 30:38.575
Guess who. Did you miss me?

30:38.749 --> 30:41.448
I see you found
a new town to live in.

30:41.622 --> 30:43.493
It reminds me a lot of
where we grew up.

30:43.667 --> 30:45.060
Oh, do we know each other?

30:45.234 --> 30:46.670
[caller] We sure do.

30:46.845 --> 30:49.151
In fact, I was just
in Woodsboro last night.

30:49.325 --> 30:51.850
Things got a little... heated.

30:52.024 --> 30:54.243
But I’m here
in Pine Grove now.

30:54.417 --> 30:55.897
Yeah? What brings you here?

30:56.071 --> 30:57.768
[caller] You, Sidney.

30:57.943 --> 31:01.685
You were missed in New York.
It’s not the same without you.

31:01.860 --> 31:04.166
I guess you couldn’t
be bothered now that you’re

31:04.340 --> 31:07.256
so busy with a husband
and family.

31:07.430 --> 31:08.910
Well, you sure know
a lot about me

31:09.084 --> 31:10.651
for another asshole
hiding behind

31:10.825 --> 31:12.479
a fake number
and a voice changer.

31:12.653 --> 31:16.396
[caller] Oh, I’m not hiding,
Sidney. Not this time.

31:16.570 --> 31:18.659
[phone chiming]

31:20.617 --> 31:22.184
[inhales shakily]

31:25.187 --> 31:27.233
Surprise, Sidney.

31:29.452 --> 31:31.106
Do you need a minute? Oh!
Oh, my gosh.

31:31.280 --> 31:32.978
It looks like you need
a minute. I’ll wait.

31:33.152 --> 31:34.762
[scoffs]

31:34.936 --> 31:36.982
Nice try. Stu Macher is dead.

31:37.156 --> 31:40.289
Oh, gosh.
I’m gonna agree to
disagree with you there.

31:40.463 --> 31:41.812
[chuckles]

31:41.987 --> 31:44.424
Oh, my God!
It is so good to see you.

31:44.598 --> 31:47.122
I always had
a thing for you, Sid!

31:47.296 --> 31:48.297
[giggles]

31:48.471 --> 31:50.734
It’s gonna be so much fun.

31:50.909 --> 31:54.738
Just like the old days,
except now there’s no Billy
or Randy or Tatum.

31:54.913 --> 31:56.523
Speaking of whom,
your daughter,

31:56.697 --> 31:59.613
her name’s Tatum.
That is so adorable.

31:59.787 --> 32:04.313
I mean, It’s a little weird or
whatever, but it’s supercute.

32:04.487 --> 32:06.402
And she is

32:07.708 --> 32:09.579
so pretty.

32:09.753 --> 32:11.712
Do not talk about my daughter.

32:11.886 --> 32:13.366
Oh. Okay, yeah.

32:13.540 --> 32:15.455
[stutters] I should definitely
tell you, though,

32:15.629 --> 32:18.284
I am currently outside of
her high school theater.

32:19.154 --> 32:21.287
Don’t you fucking dare!

32:21.461 --> 32:23.071
It’s showtime, bitch.

32:23.245 --> 32:25.117
[dramatic music playing]

32:25.813 --> 32:27.162
Hey, Chief.

32:28.424 --> 32:29.904
You’re gonna want to
hear this.

32:30.078 --> 32:31.862
I just got a call from
the police in Woodsboro.

32:32.037 --> 32:33.647
[phone buzzes]
[Mark] Just a sec.

32:33.821 --> 32:34.735
Hey, babe.

32:34.909 --> 32:36.084
[horn honking]

32:36.258 --> 32:37.564
You need to go to the theater
right now.

32:37.738 --> 32:39.218
[Mark] What? What--

32:39.392 --> 32:41.089
There’s a killer, Mark.
He’s going for Tatum.

32:41.263 --> 32:43.657
I’m on it. All available units
to the high school theater now!

32:43.831 --> 32:45.746
I’m on my way, babe.
Mark, hurry.

32:47.269 --> 32:49.532
[tires squeal]

32:50.229 --> 32:51.708
[siren wailing]

32:58.019 --> 32:59.020
[rattling]

33:05.461 --> 33:06.636
[door opens]

33:06.810 --> 33:08.769
[ominous music plays]

33:14.993 --> 33:17.517
[Hannah] Start with liftoffs
and landings, okay?

33:17.691 --> 33:18.735
[Aaron] Got it.

33:21.434 --> 33:22.304
Ready?

33:22.478 --> 33:23.653
Ready.

33:27.614 --> 33:29.877
[grunts] Okay, a little hard
on the landing there.

33:30.051 --> 33:31.139
[Aaron] Sorry.

33:33.315 --> 33:35.187
It’s just too jerky.

33:35.361 --> 33:37.015
- Softer.
- Got it.

33:39.626 --> 33:41.671
[clang in distance]
Huh?

33:41.845 --> 33:43.151
[Hannah] Try it again.

33:45.849 --> 33:47.677
- Okay, any day now!
- Oh.

33:51.855 --> 33:53.466
[slash]
[Aaron groans]

33:53.640 --> 33:54.989
Hey, Aaron?

33:55.163 --> 33:56.686
[thud]

34:00.125 --> 34:01.126
Hello?

34:04.433 --> 34:07.175
[scoffs]
This is my nice voice.

34:09.482 --> 34:10.700
[exclaims]

34:14.356 --> 34:15.618
Aaron?

34:24.932 --> 34:26.020
Shit.

34:28.892 --> 34:31.765
Aaron? I want to get down now.

34:31.939 --> 34:33.332
[grunting]

34:34.550 --> 34:35.638
Shit.

34:36.552 --> 34:37.771
Hello!

34:38.467 --> 34:42.341
[door opens, closes]

34:44.343 --> 34:46.475
No! No!

34:47.302 --> 34:49.087
[grunts, panting]

34:55.745 --> 34:57.791
Put me down-- [screams]

34:59.749 --> 35:01.360
[panting]

35:03.362 --> 35:04.363
This isn’t funny--

35:04.537 --> 35:05.842
[screams]

35:08.062 --> 35:09.063
Aaron!

35:09.237 --> 35:10.499
[grunting, panting]

35:14.721 --> 35:15.939
Aaron!

35:21.119 --> 35:22.163
Aaron!

35:22.337 --> 35:24.252
No! [screams]

35:24.818 --> 35:26.036
Help!

35:26.994 --> 35:27.995
Get me out!

35:28.169 --> 35:29.953
[screams] This hurts!

35:30.128 --> 35:31.041
Aaron!

35:31.216 --> 35:33.000
Hello!

35:33.174 --> 35:35.698
[grunting, panting]

35:38.136 --> 35:40.703
What the fuck?

35:41.704 --> 35:43.010
[screaming]

35:43.184 --> 35:44.185
No, wait!

35:46.579 --> 35:48.058
Shit!

35:48.755 --> 35:49.930
Oh, my God, please!

35:50.104 --> 35:51.758
[screams] No, wait!

35:51.932 --> 35:54.021
Hey, you stay away from me!

35:55.501 --> 35:56.763
Get away!

35:58.765 --> 36:00.854
No, please, wait! [screams]

36:02.595 --> 36:04.162
[screaming, crying]

36:06.816 --> 36:09.645
Please! Please!

36:12.344 --> 36:13.345
Please!

36:16.348 --> 36:19.612
Stop, please! Please, please!

36:19.786 --> 36:21.483
I don’t want to die!

36:24.530 --> 36:25.748
[ominous music plays]

36:25.922 --> 36:27.315
[Sidney] Tatum!

36:31.841 --> 36:33.756
Motherfucker!

36:36.672 --> 36:38.674
[dramatic music playing]

36:45.115 --> 36:46.987
Cover the exits!
[guards shouting]

36:47.161 --> 36:49.207
[panting]

36:50.208 --> 36:51.383
Oh, God. Okay.

36:59.521 --> 37:00.609
Tatum!

37:01.654 --> 37:03.264
Mom, what are you doing?
Oh, God!

37:03.438 --> 37:06.093
Are you okay?
Oh, good... okay... okay.

37:06.267 --> 37:08.269
[Sidney panting]

37:15.581 --> 37:17.670
[no audible dialogue]

37:17.844 --> 37:19.367
I wasn’t even here.
I had already left.

37:19.541 --> 37:20.586
He was home with me.

37:21.326 --> 37:22.370
Okay. Where were you?

37:24.372 --> 37:25.939
I was downstairs
in the costume shop.

37:26.113 --> 37:28.246
[Ben] Not when
I was there.
Wait, you were here?

37:28.420 --> 37:29.812
No, he left and I was there.

37:29.986 --> 37:32.206
But I didn’t see you.

37:32.380 --> 37:34.426
I was in the dressing rooms.

37:34.600 --> 37:35.688
The whole time?

37:36.732 --> 37:39.648
No. Not the whole time.

37:39.822 --> 37:42.390
I went home,
had a light dinner,
Aperol Spritz.

37:42.564 --> 37:45.175
My God, who would do
something like this?

37:45.350 --> 37:47.265
We don’t even
have an understudy.

37:47.439 --> 37:50.224
- Hey.
- Hey.

37:50.398 --> 37:52.487
So, the killer fled.

37:52.661 --> 37:55.011
Whoever did this
knew their way around here.

37:55.185 --> 37:57.362
It was well-thought-out
and executed.

37:57.536 --> 37:58.928
What about the kids?
Did you call your mom?

37:59.102 --> 38:00.800
I called.

38:00.974 --> 38:03.150
The entire Denver police force
is with them, they’re safe.

38:04.760 --> 38:06.414
Two teens are dead.

38:06.588 --> 38:08.373
Mark, what the fuck?

38:08.547 --> 38:10.766
[Sidney sniffling]

38:10.940 --> 38:12.202
You are not alone.

38:12.899 --> 38:14.248
We got this.

38:15.467 --> 38:17.904
If this is Stu...
It’s not Stu.

38:18.078 --> 38:21.386
It’s not.
He is buried in Woodsboro.

38:21.560 --> 38:23.562
Look, we are taking that
phone call that you recorded,

38:23.736 --> 38:25.390
we’re sending it
to the state police.

38:25.564 --> 38:27.653
They have the resources
to determine who it is.

38:27.827 --> 38:29.002
We are gonna get him.

38:30.438 --> 38:32.614
Isn’t Ben a computer junkie?

38:33.963 --> 38:35.574
[Mark] Aren’t all kids?

38:35.748 --> 38:39.099
He applied to Carnegie Mellon
to study computer science.

38:39.273 --> 38:42.276
I hear you.
But anybody can do
deepfakes these days.

38:42.450 --> 38:43.625
[sighs]

38:43.799 --> 38:45.366
Why don’t you get Tatum?

38:45.540 --> 38:47.194
Just give me a minute and then
we’ll get out of here.

38:51.764 --> 38:53.200
[Sidney]
Tatum, we’re going.

38:54.549 --> 38:55.550
Not you.

38:56.725 --> 38:58.205
Mom.
Answer’s no.

38:58.379 --> 38:59.380
But, Mrs. Evans--

38:59.554 --> 39:00.555
No.

39:04.037 --> 39:05.908
It’s okay.
You go with your family.

39:07.301 --> 39:08.476
I’ll call you.

39:16.441 --> 39:17.964
Why do you treat him
like that?

39:19.052 --> 39:19.966
He’s not a killer.

39:20.140 --> 39:21.097
You don’t know that.

39:21.271 --> 39:24.405
Not everyone is Billy Loomis.

39:24.579 --> 39:25.928
Just because you can’t
trust people,

39:26.102 --> 39:27.930
doesn’t mean people can’t
be trusted.

39:28.888 --> 39:30.019
We’re not doing this here.

39:34.197 --> 39:36.199
[suspenseful music playing]

39:45.121 --> 39:47.385
They’ll sweep the house.
Yeah. We’ll be quick, Chief.

40:08.884 --> 40:09.842
[deputy] All clear.

40:10.886 --> 40:12.148
We’re gonna
secure the neighborhood.

40:12.322 --> 40:13.411
Great.
We’ll only be a few minutes.

40:13.585 --> 40:14.586
Come on.
Thank you.

40:18.633 --> 40:20.505
Grab your stuff.
You leave in five.

40:21.636 --> 40:24.160
Wait. You’re not
coming with us?

40:24.334 --> 40:26.424
It’s my job to catch
whoever’s doing this.

40:37.783 --> 40:40.699
[ominous music plays]

40:40.873 --> 40:42.352
[music stops]

40:42.527 --> 40:43.484
Where’s your go bag?

40:43.658 --> 40:45.660
I unpacked it
a long time ago.

40:45.834 --> 40:47.096
Damn it, Tatum.

40:49.185 --> 40:50.317
[sighs]

40:52.232 --> 40:53.581
So, what? We just run?

40:53.755 --> 40:55.017
[sighs]

40:55.191 --> 40:56.628
Yes, we do.

40:56.802 --> 40:59.195
I thought the great
Sidney Prescott never ran.

40:59.369 --> 41:00.719
With you it’s different.

41:01.502 --> 41:02.938
They killed Hannah, Mom.

41:03.112 --> 41:05.680
We can’t just leave.
Listen, I know this story,

41:05.854 --> 41:08.291
and if we stay,
more people will die.

41:08.466 --> 41:11.425
I’m sorry, but I’m not gonna
risk you getting hurt.

41:13.383 --> 41:14.384
Why didn’t you warn me?

41:14.559 --> 41:16.474
About what?
All of this!

41:16.648 --> 41:19.302
If-If I was ready,
maybe I could have saved her.

41:19.477 --> 41:20.826
Maybe I could have
done something.

41:21.000 --> 41:22.392
If you need anything else,
pack it.

41:22.567 --> 41:24.307
Mom, why can’t you just
trust me?

41:24.482 --> 41:26.745
We need to go! Okay?

41:32.620 --> 41:34.143
Here, take these.

41:34.317 --> 41:35.797
Why did you
turn the light out?

41:36.624 --> 41:37.582
I thought you did.

41:39.975 --> 41:41.803
[ominous music playing]

41:41.977 --> 41:42.978
Tatum.

41:43.152 --> 41:44.327
Stay behind me.

41:50.812 --> 41:51.813
[Mark whispering] Tatum.

41:54.033 --> 41:55.077
Tatum.

41:57.819 --> 41:59.125
[panting]

42:02.084 --> 42:03.346
Dad.

42:06.654 --> 42:08.743
Please, leave her alone.

42:12.530 --> 42:14.009
Mark, put the gun down.

42:21.451 --> 42:23.802
[Mark]
Hon, it’s gonna be okay.

42:23.976 --> 42:24.890
Just look at me.

42:29.155 --> 42:30.504
[Sidney]
It’s me that you want.

42:30.678 --> 42:33.028
You just-- you let her go.

42:38.077 --> 42:39.295
Drop!
[Tatum screams]

42:39.469 --> 42:40.688
[Mark grunts]

42:42.255 --> 42:43.212
[Mark yells]

42:43.909 --> 42:45.519
[grunting]

42:55.703 --> 42:57.618
[grunting]

43:02.710 --> 43:03.668
Mark!
Dad!

43:03.842 --> 43:05.452
[groaning]

43:10.588 --> 43:11.676
Run!

43:15.114 --> 43:16.594
[panting] This way!

43:19.248 --> 43:21.120
[Tatum]
What-What are you doing?

43:23.383 --> 43:24.645
Fuck off!

43:28.606 --> 43:30.695
Where are we?
We’re safe in here.

43:37.919 --> 43:39.834
You sure he can’t get inside?
Yeah.

43:40.008 --> 43:41.357
What is that?
It’s another way out.

43:41.531 --> 43:42.968
I need to get your dad.
You stay here.

43:43.142 --> 43:44.447
No, you can’t leave me, Mom!

43:45.623 --> 43:46.580
[thud][screams]

43:46.754 --> 43:48.060
Let me go with you, please!

43:48.234 --> 43:49.757
Okay, hurry.

43:57.069 --> 43:58.070
[Tatum groans]

44:01.551 --> 44:02.770
[whispering]
Down to the end. Go.

44:02.944 --> 44:03.945
Okay.

44:05.381 --> 44:07.035
[floorboards creak]

44:09.385 --> 44:10.865
[tapping]

44:12.650 --> 44:13.955
[whispers] Shh.

44:19.961 --> 44:21.006
[tapping]

44:30.015 --> 44:31.277
[tapping]

44:33.801 --> 44:34.672
[gasps]

44:35.150 --> 44:36.412
[screams]

44:36.586 --> 44:38.327
Mom!
This way!

44:39.851 --> 44:40.852
[both gasp, scream]

44:41.026 --> 44:42.375
Mom!
Go, go, go!

44:44.159 --> 44:45.595
[exclaiming, panting]

44:48.990 --> 44:50.035
[screaming]

44:53.212 --> 44:54.256
Okay.

44:56.302 --> 44:58.608
[both panting]

45:02.743 --> 45:04.092
Shh-- [gasps]

45:04.266 --> 45:05.485
[screams]

45:11.186 --> 45:12.013
Go, go, go!

45:20.630 --> 45:22.023
[screams]
Mom!

45:23.155 --> 45:24.156
Go!

45:44.002 --> 45:45.786
[panting] Okay. This way.

45:52.793 --> 45:54.403
[Mark yells]

45:54.969 --> 45:56.579
[grunting]

46:08.113 --> 46:09.462
Get the police! Go!
Mom!

46:09.636 --> 46:11.986
Help! Somebody help us!

46:12.465 --> 46:14.249
[grunting]

46:36.228 --> 46:38.099
Hey, are you okay?
[panting]

46:38.273 --> 46:40.362
Are you okay?
Yeah.

46:40.536 --> 46:42.408
God, I love you.
I love you.

46:42.582 --> 46:44.584
[dramatic music playing]

46:47.674 --> 46:48.893
Did I get him?

46:49.415 --> 46:50.329
You got him!

46:50.503 --> 46:52.026
Chad, get the camera now.

46:52.200 --> 46:53.549
Mindy, set up for a remote.

46:53.723 --> 46:55.247
Ma’am, you need to stay
inside your vehicle.

46:55.421 --> 46:57.031
You need to get out
of my face.

46:57.597 --> 46:59.120
Mom! Dad!

47:01.993 --> 47:03.603
Are you okay?
I’m okay.

47:03.777 --> 47:05.953
Oh, that was horrifying.
That was awesome.

47:06.127 --> 47:07.868
Grab the camera.
We need B-roll of everything.

47:08.042 --> 47:09.783
You have to be ready
at all times.

47:09.957 --> 47:12.090
In my defense,
I wasn’t exactly expecting

47:12.264 --> 47:13.787
to be part
of vehicular manslaughter

47:13.961 --> 47:15.354
the second we roll into town,

47:15.528 --> 47:17.356
but next time...
next time I will be prepared.

47:17.530 --> 47:19.575
[Sidney panting]

47:20.750 --> 47:21.969
Hey.

47:24.493 --> 47:26.800
Chief, you gonna be okay?
Put pressure on it.

47:26.974 --> 47:28.628
Just sit still for a minute.

47:31.718 --> 47:33.285
You’re bleeding.

47:33.459 --> 47:34.721
Your point?

47:34.895 --> 47:37.115
[emotional music playing]

47:41.946 --> 47:42.947
How’s Mark?

47:43.121 --> 47:45.166
It takes a lot
to bring him down.

47:47.212 --> 47:48.909
[sighs]

47:49.083 --> 47:50.868
Gale, he said he was Stu.

47:51.956 --> 47:53.261
I’m sorry. What did you say?

47:53.783 --> 47:54.784
Stu.

47:57.875 --> 47:59.050
Stu Macher?

47:59.224 --> 48:01.095
Dead Stu Macher?

48:03.054 --> 48:04.577
Let’s unmask this fucker.

48:04.751 --> 48:07.406
[ominous music playing]

48:07.580 --> 48:08.886
- Chief?
- Do it.

48:13.673 --> 48:15.283
Who is that?

48:15.457 --> 48:18.765
I don’t know, but I saw him
today in the coffee shop.

48:18.939 --> 48:20.593
Are you sure?
Yeah.

48:20.767 --> 48:23.596
[Mindy] Nobody knows the guy?
Okay, that’s weird.

48:23.770 --> 48:26.468
That is weird. It’s always
someone you know.

48:26.642 --> 48:28.601
[sirens blaring]

48:28.775 --> 48:30.298
[mysterious music playing]

48:30.472 --> 48:31.996
[indistinct police chatter]

48:32.170 --> 48:34.259
[Chad] You want more B-roll?
We could make a whole movie.

48:34.433 --> 48:35.825
[Gale]
I don’t know what to say.

48:36.000 --> 48:38.611
I meant to brake
and I hit the gas.

48:45.226 --> 48:46.924
Karl Allen Gibbs.

48:47.098 --> 48:49.274
He escaped from Fallbrook
Psychiatric Hospital
two weeks ago.

48:49.448 --> 48:50.884
Triple murderer.

48:51.058 --> 48:54.105
Any idea why he’d come after
you or your family?

48:54.279 --> 48:56.281
No.
Thanks, Cooke.

48:57.064 --> 48:58.152
Chief.

48:59.240 --> 49:00.241
[sighs]

49:04.854 --> 49:06.117
Well...

49:06.291 --> 49:07.640
He’s not gonna
hurt anyone else.

49:07.814 --> 49:09.337
No.

49:10.686 --> 49:11.949
This was too easy.

49:13.559 --> 49:14.560
There’s always more than one.

49:14.734 --> 49:15.648
Sidney,

49:15.822 --> 49:17.519
Stu Macher is dead.

49:18.390 --> 49:20.218
[sighs]

49:20.392 --> 49:21.959
Watch Tatum for a minute.

49:24.918 --> 49:27.181
[reporter 1] Sidney. Sidney!

49:27.355 --> 49:29.705
One question for you, Sidney!

49:29.879 --> 49:31.055
Can we have a word?

49:32.273 --> 49:35.363
Sidney! What’s going on?
Over here!

49:36.625 --> 49:38.062
[reporter 2]
Can you tell us anything?

49:38.236 --> 49:40.325
What’s happening, Sidney?
What’s going on?

49:40.499 --> 49:41.500
Sidney!

49:46.984 --> 49:49.551
The network texted.
They want us to go live.

49:49.725 --> 49:52.511
I’ll go get Gale.
No! Don’t.

49:52.685 --> 49:54.252
No. No, I’m not doing this.
Yes.

49:54.426 --> 49:56.384
They didn’t specify
it had to be Gale.

49:56.558 --> 49:59.300
You’ll get us fired!
Do it! Come on!

49:59.474 --> 50:01.215
Fine.
[clears throat]

50:02.390 --> 50:05.524
Three, two, one-- Oh, boy.

50:07.395 --> 50:09.876
You try that again, and I’ll
rip both your throats out.

50:10.050 --> 50:11.095
Got it?
Copy that.

50:11.269 --> 50:13.358
We just learned
that Gale Weathers

50:13.532 --> 50:16.448
from the now defunct talk show
Good Morning with
Gale Weathersis in town.

50:16.622 --> 50:17.840
Excuse me, Miss Weathers.

50:18.015 --> 50:19.799
Robbie Rivers, WFPO.
May I ask--

50:19.973 --> 50:22.149
Fuck the fuck off.
Okay.

50:22.323 --> 50:24.760
You two are a familiar sight.
What are you doing in town?

50:25.805 --> 50:26.675
Just passing through.

50:26.849 --> 50:28.590
With Gale Weathers?

50:28.764 --> 50:31.419
And you just happened
to run over
an escaped mental patient

50:31.593 --> 50:33.508
in front
of Sidney Evans’s home?

50:33.682 --> 50:35.336
What’s really
going on here?

50:35.510 --> 50:37.034
Why don’t you
get your own story, Robbie.

50:37.208 --> 50:39.297
Yeah, we’re not here
to do it for you.

50:40.515 --> 50:43.083
Come on, give a small-town
reporter his big break!

50:47.087 --> 50:49.698
Hey, Sidney.

50:49.872 --> 50:52.527
I’m so sorry this is happening
again, Mrs. Prescott.

50:53.789 --> 50:55.400
Mrs. Evans, Lucas.

50:55.574 --> 50:57.532
Right, yeah. Uh...

50:57.706 --> 50:58.881
Sorry, that’s what I meant.

50:59.882 --> 51:01.493
Lucas, do you know
anything about A.I.?

51:01.667 --> 51:04.017
A.I.? Uh, I refuse.

51:04.191 --> 51:06.802
That is the death
of civilization. [chuckles]

51:06.976 --> 51:08.717
[Jessica]
Why are you asking that?

51:09.718 --> 51:10.893
Just be careful, Jess.

51:11.068 --> 51:12.373
Keep your doors locked.

51:14.506 --> 51:16.290
[Jessica sighs]
Okay, come on, let’s go.

51:16.986 --> 51:18.031
[gasps]

51:19.641 --> 51:20.816
Oh, you’re Gale Weathers. Hey.

51:20.990 --> 51:23.080
And who are you?
Uh...

51:23.645 --> 51:24.646
I’m Lucas.

51:25.430 --> 51:26.605
What are you doing here?

51:26.779 --> 51:29.086
He’s my son,
and we live next door.

51:29.260 --> 51:30.609
We’re friends
of the family.
Hmm.

51:30.783 --> 51:31.827
[Lucas] Yeah.

51:32.654 --> 51:34.265
You like horror movies, Lucas?

51:34.439 --> 51:36.310
Yeah, I lo-- I love them.

51:36.484 --> 51:38.095
Especially the Stabmovies?

51:38.269 --> 51:39.618
Yeah,
I know them inside and out.

51:39.792 --> 51:42.055
What are you doing?
Mom, it’s Gale Weathers.

51:42.229 --> 51:45.232
The Stabmovies were based
on her true crime bestseller,
The Woodsboro Murders.

51:45.406 --> 51:47.930
I know, but I don’t like
the way she’s looking at you.

51:48.105 --> 51:51.195
Please leave my son out of
whatever it is you’re doing.

51:52.500 --> 51:53.545
Sorry, kid,

51:53.719 --> 51:55.155
but you know how this works.

51:55.329 --> 51:56.243
Yeah.

51:56.417 --> 51:58.724
Everyone’s a suspect.

51:58.898 --> 52:02.206
Well, yeah, but you killed
the killer. He’s dead.

52:02.380 --> 52:03.381
Hmm.

52:04.773 --> 52:06.601
How do you know
there’s just one?

52:08.255 --> 52:09.169
Excuse me.

52:09.343 --> 52:11.693
[scoffs]
Whoa.

52:11.867 --> 52:15.219
Until this is over, I want you
to stay away from this house.

52:16.089 --> 52:17.264
Come on, let’s go.

52:22.704 --> 52:24.706
[Sidney]
How did you know to come?

52:24.880 --> 52:27.405
When the news broke
about the two murders
at the Macher house,

52:27.579 --> 52:31.060
a flock of reporters
raced to get there, but...

52:31.235 --> 52:33.846
my Sidney-sense told me
that Woodsboro was played out.

52:34.020 --> 52:37.806
Mark is having
the recorded calls analyzed
to confirm they’re fake.

52:37.980 --> 52:39.852
Is it possible
they’re real?

52:40.026 --> 52:41.897
Could Stu be alive?

52:42.071 --> 52:45.640
That would be
the better story,
but it’s... too far-fetched.

52:45.814 --> 52:46.859
[Gale] Hmm.

52:50.210 --> 52:51.516
What’s going on?

52:51.690 --> 52:54.214
Oh, I just have
some nerve damage from the...

52:54.388 --> 52:56.390
from the attack in New York.

52:56.564 --> 52:57.739
You’re lucky you sat
that one out.

52:57.913 --> 52:59.524
It-It was brutal.

53:00.394 --> 53:01.395
Thank you.

53:01.569 --> 53:02.657
It’s nice to meet you, Tatum.

53:02.831 --> 53:04.572
Mmm. Tatum?

53:05.704 --> 53:07.358
Tatum as in...
That Tatum.

53:07.532 --> 53:08.750
Yeah.

53:08.924 --> 53:10.056
What do you two do for Gale?

53:10.230 --> 53:11.579
We’re her hot interns.

53:11.753 --> 53:13.451
Ever since she got axed,

53:13.625 --> 53:15.192
she’s been trying to
go back to her roots.

53:15.366 --> 53:18.238
So she’s rebranding herself
as a crime reporter.

53:18.412 --> 53:19.805
She’s teaching us
all she knows about the biz.

53:19.979 --> 53:22.068
Don’t say "biz."Yep.

53:22.242 --> 53:24.766
It’s more like we’re showing
Gale the ropes
of making premium content.

53:24.940 --> 53:26.072
Don’t say "content."

53:26.246 --> 53:27.726
It’s going great.

53:27.900 --> 53:29.031
Except Mindy keeps trying to
steal Gale’s thunder.

53:29.206 --> 53:31.338
- I’m the face of the future.
- Sure.

53:31.512 --> 53:33.993
But in the meantime,
we’re learning all about
fading careers

53:34.167 --> 53:35.647
and failed comebacks.

53:37.649 --> 53:38.954
[Gale]
Where are we gonna start?

53:40.042 --> 53:42.523
S-Start what? I’m...

53:44.177 --> 53:45.396
I’m not starting anything.

53:45.570 --> 53:48.050
We have to find out
who’s behind this.

53:48.225 --> 53:49.574
That guy in the road,
Karl Gibbs,

53:49.748 --> 53:51.228
is not some random killer.

53:51.402 --> 53:53.839
It’s always someone
connected to your past.

53:54.013 --> 53:55.188
The police can handle it.

53:55.362 --> 53:56.755
That would be
your husband.

53:56.929 --> 53:58.147
And we need to help him.

53:59.192 --> 54:00.889
Don’t you want to
know who’s behind this?

54:01.063 --> 54:03.457
Gale, I can’t anymore.

54:03.631 --> 54:06.721
I need to be with my family,
I need to know they’re safe.

54:06.895 --> 54:08.157
That’s why
you need to help me.

54:08.332 --> 54:10.508
Whoever is targeting you
is not gonna stop...

54:10.682 --> 54:12.205
[phone ringing]
...you know that.

54:16.688 --> 54:20.169
Oh, slap my face, if it
isn’t the Gale Weathers!

54:20.344 --> 54:21.606
Hi. Oh, my God,

54:21.780 --> 54:23.825
I am so sorry
your show got canceled

54:23.999 --> 54:25.653
and then you got fired.

54:25.827 --> 54:28.308
I wasn’t fired.
My contract wasn’t renewed.

54:28.482 --> 54:30.876
So don’t care.
Not even a little.

54:31.050 --> 54:33.835
Ugh. I’m so sorry for
running over your friend.

54:34.009 --> 54:35.881
Can’t do your own
dirty work, Stu?

54:36.055 --> 54:37.361
[mocking blabbering]

54:37.535 --> 54:38.927
Neither can you.

54:39.101 --> 54:42.104
You brought in some old,
irrelevant hag for backup.

54:42.279 --> 54:43.541
It’s so sad.

54:43.715 --> 54:45.064
And what happened to
the two of you?

54:45.238 --> 54:46.848
You both had so much spunk.

54:47.022 --> 54:49.460
You’re gonna die,
you A.I. asshole.

54:49.634 --> 54:51.157
We’re going to see
how fake I am

54:51.331 --> 54:53.115
when I stab you
in the fucking throat!

54:53.290 --> 54:54.813
Because I’m coming for you

54:54.987 --> 54:58.251
and I’m gonna love
every second of it.

54:58.425 --> 54:59.426
[chuckles]

55:01.602 --> 55:03.125
[sighs]

55:03.300 --> 55:05.040
That was fucking weird.

55:08.174 --> 55:09.915
Fallbrook
Psychiatric Hospital.

55:10.089 --> 55:12.134
It’s a couple hours away.
We’ll start there.

55:13.832 --> 55:14.833
There she is.

55:15.877 --> 55:17.879
I knew you were
in there somewhere.

55:18.053 --> 55:21.143
You’re right. This isn’t
gonna stop unless I stop it.

55:28.542 --> 55:30.196
I’ll be back as soon as I can.

55:30.370 --> 55:32.285
Mom, I want to go with you.

55:32.459 --> 55:34.287
No, sweetie, it’s not safe.

55:34.461 --> 55:35.419
So why are you going?

55:35.593 --> 55:36.507
Because I know what I’m doing.

55:36.681 --> 55:37.943
Mom, please.

55:38.117 --> 55:39.205
You don’t have
the skill set for this.

55:39.379 --> 55:40.902
Well, then show me.

55:41.990 --> 55:43.992
I don’t want to end up like
the other Tatum.

55:45.385 --> 55:46.386
What?

55:47.474 --> 55:48.606
You named me after a girl who

55:48.780 --> 55:51.304
got her head crushed
in a garage door.

55:51.478 --> 55:53.350
She was my friend.
And she’s dead!

55:55.264 --> 55:56.962
She was a-a victim,
not a fighter.

55:57.136 --> 55:59.356
I want to be a fighter.

55:59.530 --> 56:01.227
Honey. Listen--

56:01.401 --> 56:02.794
Nice to know what
you think of me.

56:04.361 --> 56:05.710
[exhales deeply]

56:12.151 --> 56:15.241
She just lost a friend,
so... she’s upset.

56:16.547 --> 56:18.157
I want you to keep
her away from Ben.

56:18.331 --> 56:20.464
He’s not to come over here.

56:20.638 --> 56:23.510
Someone was hiding
in the attic.
It could have been him.

56:23.684 --> 56:27.993
We are running traces on
all her friends’ cell numbers,
emails and IP’s.

56:28.167 --> 56:31.257
If Ben or any of her friends
are connected in any way

56:31.431 --> 56:32.432
we’re gonna find it.

56:36.044 --> 56:39.483
She’s right, you know.
Me protecting her from this,

56:40.353 --> 56:41.789
I made her vulnerable to it.

57:04.072 --> 57:05.117
Right.

57:06.466 --> 57:07.467
Okay.

57:08.555 --> 57:11.166
Okay, Terry. Thanks again.

57:13.691 --> 57:16.868
Woodsboro coroner says
there’s no intake form
on Stu Macher’s body.

57:17.042 --> 57:20.175
The woman who was coroner
in ’96 died three years ago,

57:20.349 --> 57:21.438
so there’s no one to ask.

57:21.612 --> 57:24.223
So it’s a case
of lost paperwork?

57:24.397 --> 57:25.833
Or stolen paperwork.

57:26.007 --> 57:27.531
Someone who wants to
make it look like Stu’s body

57:27.705 --> 57:29.097
never made it to the morgue.

57:30.403 --> 57:31.317
Or...

57:31.491 --> 57:32.840
It’s actually Stu.

57:33.014 --> 57:34.625
Let’s find out.
Yep.

57:35.756 --> 57:36.888
Here’s your pass.
Thank you.

57:37.628 --> 57:38.542
Here you go.

57:38.716 --> 57:39.717
Thanks.

57:40.979 --> 57:42.328
How can I help you?

57:42.502 --> 57:43.764
Hi, I’m Gale Weathers.

57:43.938 --> 57:45.592
I’m a reporter
for Channel 7 in New York.

57:45.766 --> 57:47.202
Mm-hmm.

57:47.376 --> 57:49.204
We’re doing a story
on Karl Gibbs.
I figured.

57:49.378 --> 57:52.512
The state police,
they were here all night
going through his stuff.

57:53.208 --> 57:54.209
Can we see his room?

57:54.949 --> 57:55.950
Well...

57:57.430 --> 57:59.693
[groans]

57:59.867 --> 58:02.130
Yeah, I guess so. Come on,
it’s right down this way.

58:03.567 --> 58:05.394
So what can you
tell us about Karl?

58:05.569 --> 58:07.135
He was
a pretty violent guy.

58:08.528 --> 58:11.400
Killed three women
about 20 years ago.

58:14.403 --> 58:16.014
Can you think of any reason
that he would

58:16.188 --> 58:18.103
go after Sidney Prescott
and her family?

58:19.452 --> 58:21.149
[Marco] No, not that I know of.

58:22.673 --> 58:23.935
I’m glad you’re okay, though.

58:24.588 --> 58:26.067
Thanks.

58:29.593 --> 58:32.552
Did you ever hear him talk
about the Ghostface killings?

58:32.726 --> 58:35.294
Or the Stabmovies,
or anything like that?

58:35.468 --> 58:36.600
Not that I remember.

58:36.774 --> 58:37.992
What about, um...

58:38.819 --> 58:39.733
him?

58:39.907 --> 58:41.866
Yeah, that’s John.

58:42.997 --> 58:44.172
John?

58:44.346 --> 58:45.522
Yeah, as in John Doe.

58:45.696 --> 58:47.524
He didn’t know his real name.

58:47.698 --> 58:49.090
He had amnesia from
the blow to the head

58:49.264 --> 58:51.049
that gave him all those scars.

58:51.223 --> 58:52.572
When did he arrive here?

58:52.746 --> 58:54.226
Well, it was before my time.

58:54.400 --> 58:58.709
I’ve been here 16 years.
So late ’90s, maybe?

58:59.927 --> 59:01.973
His room was right down there.
You want to see it?

59:02.147 --> 59:03.496
Yes.

59:03.670 --> 59:05.759
You know, h-he was a drifter.

59:05.933 --> 59:08.545
Sleeping on the streets
of California or somewhere.

59:09.894 --> 59:11.983
And then one day he snapped.

59:12.853 --> 59:15.160
Attacked a high school girl.

59:15.334 --> 59:19.207
He was declared incompetent to
stand trial and ended up here.

59:20.339 --> 59:22.646
And where is he now?
He was released.

59:24.473 --> 59:26.519
Two weeks ago.

59:26.693 --> 59:28.739
Any idea where he went
after he was released?

59:29.957 --> 59:30.871
No, I’m sorry.

59:31.045 --> 59:32.133
But for that information

59:32.307 --> 59:34.309
you’re gonna need
a court order.

59:34.483 --> 59:36.747
And I assume that John Doe
and Karl Gibbs

59:36.921 --> 59:38.400
spent a lot of time together?

59:38.575 --> 59:40.664
Oh, yeah.
No, they were good friends.

59:40.838 --> 59:41.926
Yeah.

59:42.100 --> 59:43.318
[Marco] Very close.

59:44.232 --> 59:45.538
[leaf blower blowing]

59:45.712 --> 59:46.713
Hmm.

59:58.769 --> 59:59.770
Hmm.

01:00:02.816 --> 01:00:04.035
[Mindy] Neighbor boy’s sus.

01:00:04.209 --> 01:00:06.211
He’s out there
staring at the house.

01:00:06.385 --> 01:00:07.778
Not subtle at all.

01:00:08.561 --> 01:00:10.824
I’ve gone back three days.

01:00:10.998 --> 01:00:12.434
If the killer was hiding
in the attic,

01:00:12.609 --> 01:00:14.219
he had to go into
the house at some point.

01:00:14.393 --> 01:00:16.525
Could the footage be hacked?

01:00:16.700 --> 01:00:18.615
Clearly the killer
is tech savvy.

01:00:18.789 --> 01:00:19.746
[Chad] I don’t know.
[clears throat]

01:00:19.920 --> 01:00:22.096
Uh, did you two find
the towels?

01:00:22.270 --> 01:00:23.271
You got everything you need?

01:00:23.445 --> 01:00:25.186
Yeah, the water
pressure was...

01:00:25.360 --> 01:00:27.232
top-notch, so, thank you.

01:00:27.406 --> 01:00:28.668
Yeah. Yeah, of course.

01:00:29.713 --> 01:00:31.018
So, um...

01:00:32.106 --> 01:00:33.151
Why are you here?

01:00:34.543 --> 01:00:37.155
I’m sorry, I mean,
um... [scoffs]

01:00:38.939 --> 01:00:40.288
After everything
you’ve been through,

01:00:41.246 --> 01:00:42.160
aren’t you scared?

01:00:42.334 --> 01:00:44.989
[chuckles] Scared. Necessity.

01:00:45.163 --> 01:00:48.209
My career trajectory
is to succeed
and exceed Gale Weathers.

01:00:48.383 --> 01:00:51.169
And as Woodsboro legacy,
it is our duty.

01:00:52.605 --> 01:00:54.999
Our uncle Randy was really
good friends with your mom.

01:00:55.173 --> 01:00:57.697
[Mindy] And I want to uncover
the killer this time.

01:00:57.871 --> 01:00:59.133
She has been wrong a lot.

01:00:59.307 --> 01:01:00.657
That is not supportive.

01:01:00.831 --> 01:01:04.138
Un-Uncover a killer?
How do you uncover a killer?

01:01:04.312 --> 01:01:08.403
Assemble the suspects
and then Agatha Christie them
until they break.

01:01:08.577 --> 01:01:10.405
So-- How do you
know who they are?

01:01:10.579 --> 01:01:12.973
If history is any indication,
it’s likely
one of your friends.

01:01:13.147 --> 01:01:14.322
Probably your boyfriend.

01:01:14.496 --> 01:01:15.976
[Chad] Boyfriend’s too obvious.

01:01:16.150 --> 01:01:17.543
Unless it’s by design.

01:01:17.717 --> 01:01:18.718
It’s not my boyfriend.

01:01:18.892 --> 01:01:20.415
[chuckles] That’s cute.

01:01:20.589 --> 01:01:22.591
We need to gather all the
suspects together in one room.

01:01:22.766 --> 01:01:26.030
Well, there’s
a curfew at sundown.
The whole town’s closing up.

01:01:28.467 --> 01:01:30.034
Actually, there might be a way.

01:01:30.208 --> 01:01:32.645
I just would have to figure
out how to get around my dad.

01:01:32.819 --> 01:01:34.560
[Chad] Is that possible?

01:01:34.734 --> 01:01:36.605
He is the police chief.

01:01:36.780 --> 01:01:39.478
But if we can find out
who’s doing this,
then he can go get them.

01:01:39.652 --> 01:01:41.306
If we can help, we should.

01:01:43.700 --> 01:01:44.744
I’m sick of being useless.

01:01:47.442 --> 01:01:49.053
That was Deputy Cooke.

01:01:49.227 --> 01:01:51.577
They’re set up to trace his
phone if he calls me again.

01:01:51.751 --> 01:01:53.666
So we just have to
wait for him to call?

01:01:53.840 --> 01:01:56.451
Oh, come on,
there’s got to be some way to
bait him into calling you.

01:01:58.279 --> 01:02:01.587
What if I gave you what you’ve
been asking me for since 1996?

01:02:02.980 --> 01:02:03.981
An interview.

01:02:06.548 --> 01:02:08.507
Get the fuck out of here.

01:02:08.681 --> 01:02:10.639
Look, I just need an ETA
on that court order.

01:02:10.814 --> 01:02:12.816
[Cooke] You got it, Chief.
I’ll take care of it.

01:02:12.990 --> 01:02:15.383
Good. Okay. Call me
the second Sid’s phone rings.

01:02:17.168 --> 01:02:18.082
Tatum!

01:02:18.256 --> 01:02:19.431
[clattering]

01:02:26.830 --> 01:02:28.048
[clattering]

01:04:04.318 --> 01:04:05.319
[electrical buzzing]

01:04:17.027 --> 01:04:18.550
[screams]

01:04:23.642 --> 01:04:25.078
[screaming]

01:04:33.173 --> 01:04:34.827
["Red Right Hand" playing]

01:04:35.001 --> 01:04:39.179
♪ ...to the edge of town
Go across the tracks ♪

01:04:40.746 --> 01:04:45.185
♪ Where the viaduct looms
Like a bird of doom ♪

01:04:45.359 --> 01:04:46.534
♪ As it shifts...♪

01:04:46.708 --> 01:04:49.363
[owner] Okay.
Get home safe. Bye, guys.

01:04:49.537 --> 01:04:53.585
♪ Where secrets lie
In the border fires ♪

01:04:53.759 --> 01:04:55.587
♪ In the humming wires ♪

01:04:55.761 --> 01:04:58.720
♪ Hey man, you know
You’re never coming back ♪

01:04:58.895 --> 01:05:00.897
♪ Past this square
Past the bridge ♪

01:05:01.071 --> 01:05:03.595
♪ Past the mills
Past the stacks ♪

01:05:05.945 --> 01:05:09.949
♪ On a gathering storm
Comes a tall, handsome man ♪

01:05:10.123 --> 01:05:14.780
♪ In a dusty black coat
With a red right hand ♪

01:05:17.130 --> 01:05:18.262
Hey.
Hey, Chlo.

01:05:18.436 --> 01:05:19.785
Ben and Lucas
are already here.

01:05:19.959 --> 01:05:22.831
All right. Uh,
this is Chad and Mindy.

01:05:23.006 --> 01:05:24.833
Hi. I’m Chloe. Come on in.

01:05:27.010 --> 01:05:28.968
[Chad] So your parents
own this place.

01:05:29.142 --> 01:05:31.405
[Chloe] Yes, but they
don’t know we’re here,
so we got to lay low.

01:05:32.493 --> 01:05:33.494
How you doing?

01:05:34.669 --> 01:05:36.193
[Chloe] What are
we drinking, kids?

01:05:37.455 --> 01:05:38.804
Here is...

01:05:38.978 --> 01:05:41.111
[singsongy] ...the
pepperoni and mushroom pizza.

01:05:41.285 --> 01:05:42.808
[Tatum] Thanks, Chlo.
[Chad] Thank you.

01:05:42.982 --> 01:05:44.636
So what is the deal
with you two?

01:05:44.810 --> 01:05:47.595
[Tatum] Um, they want to help
us find out who’s doing this.

01:05:47.769 --> 01:05:50.468
What, they think
it’s one of us?

01:05:50.642 --> 01:05:51.948
[Mindy chuckles]

01:05:53.862 --> 01:05:56.082
Yeah. But I don’t.

01:05:57.736 --> 01:05:59.607
So this dead dude from thirty
years ago, he is not so dead?

01:05:59.781 --> 01:06:01.479
How could Stu Macher
really be alive?

01:06:02.262 --> 01:06:03.916
Where’s he been? Under a rock?

01:06:04.090 --> 01:06:05.962
Nobody recognized him
for three decades?

01:06:06.136 --> 01:06:08.877
That’s a ridiculous retcon
for any franchise.

01:06:09.052 --> 01:06:11.880
See, this time it is
all about nostalgia.

01:06:12.055 --> 01:06:14.274
Hey, Min! We talked about
the rules thing,

01:06:14.448 --> 01:06:16.363
we said we weren’t gonna
do that anymore. We’re better
than that. So just...

01:06:16.537 --> 01:06:20.324
Okay. Whoever it is
wants to bring Sidney
out of retirement.

01:06:20.498 --> 01:06:23.414
She’s a scream queen.
Scream queens are not allowed
to have happy endings.

01:06:23.588 --> 01:06:27.287
There’s a reason they
keep putting Jamie Lee
in new Halloweenmovies.

01:06:27.461 --> 01:06:29.202
We all want to read
Wuthering Heights
again for the first time.

01:06:29.376 --> 01:06:30.682
But this is real life.

01:06:30.856 --> 01:06:32.771
Yes, exactly.

01:06:32.945 --> 01:06:35.208
This person isn’t a fan of
Stabmovies,

01:06:35.382 --> 01:06:37.906
they’re a fan of
Sidney Prescott.

01:06:38.081 --> 01:06:39.691
Not the Sidney of today, though.

01:06:39.865 --> 01:06:42.389
The Sidney
of thirty years ago.

01:06:42.563 --> 01:06:45.479
The Sidney that was killing
Ghostfaces, like, once a year.

01:06:45.653 --> 01:06:47.873
And the reason they’re using
Stu Macher to fuck with her

01:06:48.047 --> 01:06:50.484
is because he was
there at the start.

01:06:50.658 --> 01:06:54.358
The night Sidney the
Avenging Angel was born.

01:06:54.532 --> 01:06:56.360
[whistles]

01:06:56.534 --> 01:06:58.579
Or it really is Stu.
I mean, Billy Loomis
had a secret love child,

01:06:58.753 --> 01:07:00.494
so who the fuck knows anymore?

01:07:00.668 --> 01:07:02.322
- Where’d you get these calls?
- Uh...

01:07:02.496 --> 01:07:05.717
My mom’s cloud. Can you
tell if they’re fake or not?

01:07:05.891 --> 01:07:07.066
If it’s a fake,
- it’s a good one.
- Hmm.

01:07:07.240 --> 01:07:09.155
The shadows are consistent.

01:07:09.329 --> 01:07:12.550
The eyes, hands, they all have
zero artifacts or pixilation.
I mean...

01:07:12.724 --> 01:07:14.073
These might have
been live calls.

01:07:14.247 --> 01:07:17.033
All right, well,
if it is Stu Macher

01:07:17.207 --> 01:07:19.296
then we know
he has an accomplice.

01:07:19.470 --> 01:07:21.646
He can’t be in two
places at once, so...

01:07:23.300 --> 01:07:24.823
who is it?

01:07:24.997 --> 01:07:26.781
Why would any of us want to
terrorize Tatum and her mom?

01:07:26.955 --> 01:07:30.176
Why indeed. Let’s talk motive.

01:07:30.350 --> 01:07:31.699
Pardon. Thank you.

01:07:31.873 --> 01:07:34.485
Okay, Ben.
Mmm.

01:07:34.659 --> 01:07:37.183
Does Sidney truly approve
of you as Tatum’s boyfriend?

01:07:37.357 --> 01:07:40.882
Moms never like the boyfriend.
That’s Mommy 101, there.

01:07:41.057 --> 01:07:44.060
And you’re an interesting
mix of brawn and brains.

01:07:44.234 --> 01:07:46.627
Nah. I like to work out
my body and my mind, yeah.

01:07:46.801 --> 01:07:48.499
See, that’s incredibly
bizarre to say out loud.

01:07:48.673 --> 01:07:50.283
[Mindy] Chloe.

01:07:50.457 --> 01:07:52.198
Hey.
[Mindy]
Fun-loving. Everyone likes.

01:07:52.372 --> 01:07:54.679
Excellent hair.
Seemingly has no motive.

01:07:54.853 --> 01:07:56.159
That’s me.

01:07:56.333 --> 01:07:57.595
I’m not buying it.
[Chloe] Good.

01:07:57.769 --> 01:07:59.162
I don’t like a girl
that everyone likes.

01:07:59.336 --> 01:08:00.772
It’s boring.

01:08:00.946 --> 01:08:03.296
Oh. See? That’s motive.

01:08:03.470 --> 01:08:06.125
Right? Boredom? Now we’re
in Stu Macher territory.

01:08:06.299 --> 01:08:08.301
[Mindy]
And you, weird boy.
Okay.

01:08:08.475 --> 01:08:12.000
You’ve displayed
an unsettling obsession with
all things Sidney Prescott.

01:08:12.175 --> 01:08:14.002
She’s a pinnacle in
the true-crime lexicon.

01:08:14.177 --> 01:08:15.569
I’m not obsessed.
I’m just...

01:08:15.743 --> 01:08:18.659
I’m, uh, fascinated.

01:08:18.833 --> 01:08:21.227
Splitting hairs,
young man.

01:08:21.401 --> 01:08:22.794
Okay, my money’s on boyfriend.

01:08:22.968 --> 01:08:24.187
Yeah, my bet’s
on creepy kid.

01:08:24.361 --> 01:08:25.710
Okay,
I’m pretty fucking sick of

01:08:25.884 --> 01:08:27.407
all this "creepy" shit,
all right?

01:08:27.581 --> 01:08:28.887
I’m not creepy.

01:08:29.061 --> 01:08:31.237
Creepy is kind of hot.

01:08:31.411 --> 01:08:32.412
[gasps]

01:08:33.544 --> 01:08:35.023
Oh.
Hey.

01:08:35.198 --> 01:08:36.199
Hey.

01:08:37.678 --> 01:08:39.027
Can I have another beer?

01:08:39.202 --> 01:08:40.551
You can have
whatever you want.

01:08:44.642 --> 01:08:47.253
[Robbie]
And per our discussion,
this is my exclusive.

01:08:47.427 --> 01:08:49.255
That was the deal.
[Gale] Yeah, yeah. Got it.

01:08:49.429 --> 01:08:51.388
[Robbie] Okay.
[Gale exhales] There you go.

01:08:51.562 --> 01:08:52.606
Oh, okay.

01:08:52.780 --> 01:08:54.565
Oh. There.

01:08:54.739 --> 01:08:55.870
[Robbie sighs]

01:08:56.044 --> 01:08:57.655
All right,
I have three cameras on you.

01:08:57.829 --> 01:08:59.483
We’ll be operating from
the control room.

01:08:59.657 --> 01:09:02.355
We need your phone,
so when he calls...

01:09:03.182 --> 01:09:05.445
Thank you.
All right, ladies,

01:09:05.619 --> 01:09:08.970
we’ll be ready to break into
every affiliate in the state
on your go.

01:09:09.841 --> 01:09:11.799
Jesus, this is
fucking awesome!

01:09:12.626 --> 01:09:13.801
[Gale] Okay.

01:09:13.975 --> 01:09:15.847
Let’s just hope that
Stu is watching.

01:09:16.500 --> 01:09:17.544
Ready?

01:09:17.718 --> 01:09:19.807
You gonna play nice?
Of course not.

01:09:19.981 --> 01:09:22.941
I’ve been waiting for this
interview for thirty years.

01:09:23.115 --> 01:09:24.769
And three, two...

01:09:24.943 --> 01:09:27.075
[theme music playing]

01:09:27.250 --> 01:09:31.384
Hi, I’m Gale Weathers
here for an exclusive interview
with Sidney Prescott.

01:09:31.558 --> 01:09:33.691
[phone chimes]
[Lucas, Chloe chattering]

01:09:35.606 --> 01:09:37.085
What the hell?

01:09:37.260 --> 01:09:39.914
My mom’s going live on TV.
Channel 7.

01:09:40.088 --> 01:09:41.133
Oh.

01:09:44.180 --> 01:09:46.704
Welcome, Sidney. Hi.
Hi, Gale.

01:09:46.878 --> 01:09:51.187
So everyone knows you as
the survivor of
many brutal attacks.

01:09:51.361 --> 01:09:55.278
And I understand that
you and your family
are once again a target.

01:09:55.452 --> 01:09:57.454
Can you explain
what’s happening?

01:09:57.628 --> 01:09:59.630
My family and I
have been attacked twice now

01:09:59.804 --> 01:10:02.328
by someone claiming to be
Stu Macher.

01:10:02.502 --> 01:10:04.635
But Stu was
killed in Woodsboro

01:10:04.809 --> 01:10:07.855
the night that he
and Billy Loomis attacked you.

01:10:08.029 --> 01:10:11.598
Yes, but now
I’m not so sure.

01:10:11.772 --> 01:10:13.774
Is that why you’re doing
this interview?

01:10:13.948 --> 01:10:16.690
I want to talk to him.
What would you
like to say?

01:10:16.864 --> 01:10:19.563
I want to know
what he wants.

01:10:19.737 --> 01:10:22.130
Why he’s doing this
after all of these years.

01:10:22.305 --> 01:10:23.871
I want him to know that

01:10:25.090 --> 01:10:26.657
this doesn’t need to continue.

01:10:26.831 --> 01:10:28.441
Zoom in.
Tighter, tighter.

01:10:28.615 --> 01:10:30.791
Whatever you need, let’s talk.

01:10:30.965 --> 01:10:32.010
Hmm.

01:10:33.533 --> 01:10:35.492
Maybe he’s too much of
a little bitch.

01:10:36.580 --> 01:10:39.104
He always was the sidekick,
never the lead.

01:10:41.367 --> 01:10:43.021
Is that what it is?

01:10:43.195 --> 01:10:46.329
You want to be the lead?
Well, here you go.

01:10:46.503 --> 01:10:48.331
Call me. You have a platform.

01:10:48.505 --> 01:10:49.680
Oh, shit.

01:10:54.293 --> 01:10:57.427
Maybe he hasn’t tuned in yet.
Let’s keep talking.

01:10:58.732 --> 01:11:00.908
You and I have known
each other a long time.

01:11:01.909 --> 01:11:03.607
A very long time, yes.
[clears throat]

01:11:03.781 --> 01:11:05.478
How would you describe
our relationship?

01:11:06.914 --> 01:11:08.568
Complicated but enduring.

01:11:10.091 --> 01:11:12.006
You wrote a book,
Out of Darkness,

01:11:12.180 --> 01:11:14.008
about healing your trauma.

01:11:14.182 --> 01:11:16.576
And yet you have
completely disappeared

01:11:16.750 --> 01:11:19.579
from the public eye
for years now. Why?

01:11:19.753 --> 01:11:23.366
It just seemed
the more I talked about it,
the more darkness came.

01:11:23.540 --> 01:11:24.541
Mmm.

01:11:24.715 --> 01:11:25.977
You have three children.

01:11:26.151 --> 01:11:28.458
Tatum being your oldest.
She’s seventeen?

01:11:28.632 --> 01:11:30.460
I’d rather not talk about
my children.

01:11:30.634 --> 01:11:34.246
Tatum is the same age
that you were
when this whole thing started.

01:11:34.420 --> 01:11:36.553
That must have
a huge significance for you.

01:11:36.727 --> 01:11:38.816
Like I said, I don’t want to
talk about my kids.

01:11:38.990 --> 01:11:41.122
[Gale]
And you named your kid Tatum

01:11:41.297 --> 01:11:44.996
after the young girl who was
brutally murdered
all those years ago.

01:11:45.170 --> 01:11:48.695
I named her after a childhood
friend whom I loved dearly.

01:11:50.697 --> 01:11:53.004
She was the last friend
I ever trusted.

01:11:54.832 --> 01:11:55.876
Mmm.

01:11:56.790 --> 01:11:57.965
Sidney, do you ever
worry about

01:11:58.139 --> 01:12:00.141
passing your trauma on
to your children?

01:12:00.316 --> 01:12:01.665
Or, even worse yet,

01:12:01.839 --> 01:12:03.667
that they would be
the target of future killings?

01:12:03.841 --> 01:12:05.103
Oh, shit.

01:12:05.277 --> 01:12:06.974
[Gale] Sidney?
Okay, Gale, stop.

01:12:09.760 --> 01:12:11.936
Where’s she going?
Okay, we’ll be right back.

01:12:12.110 --> 01:12:14.504
Or maybe not. Cut.

01:12:14.678 --> 01:12:15.766
All right.

01:12:15.940 --> 01:12:17.985
Um... Go to the outro
and stand by.

01:12:18.159 --> 01:12:19.726
[theme music playing]
Wh--

01:12:22.468 --> 01:12:23.556
That was unfair.

01:12:24.122 --> 01:12:26.080
And dangerous!

01:12:26.254 --> 01:12:28.561
But you disappeared, Sid.
People want to know.

01:12:28.735 --> 01:12:30.171
I want to know!

01:12:31.259 --> 01:12:33.305
- I’m sorry.
- Are you?

01:12:33.479 --> 01:12:36.613
What if I had asked you
about Dewey on live TV?

01:12:36.787 --> 01:12:37.701
What would you say?

01:12:37.875 --> 01:12:40.051
Well, I’d say I’m fine.

01:12:41.748 --> 01:12:44.708
Because that’s what I
tell myself 500 times a day

01:12:44.882 --> 01:12:46.710
just to get through the day.

01:13:07.078 --> 01:13:09.950
This has been a Robbie Rivers
exclusive with Gale Weathers

01:13:10.124 --> 01:13:12.649
and Pine Grove’s very
own Sidney Prescott Evans.

01:13:12.823 --> 01:13:14.128
We will be monitoring--

01:13:14.302 --> 01:13:16.000
That was intense.

01:13:17.654 --> 01:13:18.655
Yeah.

01:13:19.525 --> 01:13:20.526
Are you okay?

01:13:23.790 --> 01:13:25.270
I’m sorry this is happening.

01:13:26.184 --> 01:13:28.534
And this--
This was a dumb idea.

01:13:28.708 --> 01:13:30.057
How far is the TV station?

01:13:30.231 --> 01:13:31.972
I just really want to be with
my mom right now.

01:13:32.146 --> 01:13:33.626
We’re super close.
I mean, I’ll take you.

01:13:34.279 --> 01:13:35.672
Okay.

01:13:35.846 --> 01:13:36.890
[phone ringing]

01:13:38.283 --> 01:13:39.850
[breathes deeply]

01:13:42.548 --> 01:13:43.767
We’re not on air.

01:13:43.941 --> 01:13:45.856
And this needs to be
on air.
Hello?

01:13:46.030 --> 01:13:48.554
Aw, Sid, do you need a hug?

01:13:48.728 --> 01:13:50.295
[mocking crying]

01:13:50.469 --> 01:13:51.862
We’ve been waiting for you.

01:13:52.036 --> 01:13:53.167
Why? So I can
stay on the phone

01:13:53.341 --> 01:13:54.821
long enough for you to
trace the call?

01:13:54.995 --> 01:13:57.389
Yes, dumbass! Or you could
just tell us where you are.

01:13:57.563 --> 01:14:00.392
Great. I am at Parker’s Tavern

01:14:00.566 --> 01:14:02.220
with your daughter.

01:14:03.221 --> 01:14:04.657
My daughter’s not at Parker’s.

01:14:04.831 --> 01:14:06.311
Well, she’s definitely not
at home.

01:14:06.485 --> 01:14:08.139
[chuckles] She broke curfew.

01:14:08.313 --> 01:14:10.097
She’s a bad bitch.

01:14:10.837 --> 01:14:12.186
I’m gonna punish her.

01:14:13.187 --> 01:14:14.493
Fuck.

01:14:14.667 --> 01:14:16.234
Is that it?
Is he gonna call back?

01:14:16.408 --> 01:14:17.757
Because you said
this was my story.

01:14:17.931 --> 01:14:19.063
Where’s the story, Gale?
Stop!

01:14:19.237 --> 01:14:20.978
You need to
call the police right now,

01:14:21.152 --> 01:14:23.110
tell them to go to
Parker’s Tavern.

01:14:23.981 --> 01:14:24.982
Sidney!

01:14:26.418 --> 01:14:27.680
Sidney!

01:14:28.725 --> 01:14:29.987
Oh, fuck.

01:14:30.161 --> 01:14:32.119
Mark, Tatum went
to Chloe’s restaurant.

01:14:32.293 --> 01:14:33.164
She’s in trouble.

01:14:33.338 --> 01:14:34.687
Where are you?

01:14:34.861 --> 01:14:35.775
Damn it!

01:14:35.949 --> 01:14:37.473
[breathing heavily]

01:14:39.736 --> 01:14:40.737
Oh, fuck.

01:14:42.521 --> 01:14:44.436
[intense music playing]

01:14:51.965 --> 01:14:52.966
Thanks.

01:15:03.063 --> 01:15:04.238
What is this?
Hmm?

01:15:04.412 --> 01:15:05.849
Oh, uh...

01:15:06.023 --> 01:15:09.026
[Tatum]
Did you create this?
[Ben] What? No.

01:15:09.200 --> 01:15:11.507
I created that one just
to see if it was possible.

01:15:11.681 --> 01:15:13.987
I can’t wait to fucking
kill you, Sidney Prescott,

01:15:14.161 --> 01:15:15.772
and your daughter.

01:15:15.946 --> 01:15:18.992
And I’m gonna love
every second of it, you bitch!

01:15:19.166 --> 01:15:20.167
Tate.

01:15:20.341 --> 01:15:22.648
It was you.
No, it wasn’t.

01:15:22.822 --> 01:15:24.345
[groans]
[gasps]

01:15:24.520 --> 01:15:25.956
Tate.
[grunts]

01:15:39.317 --> 01:15:41.667
You know, not exactly
a roaring success, Min.

01:15:41.841 --> 01:15:43.408
We still have no idea
who the killer is.

01:15:43.582 --> 01:15:45.236
Creepy kid still has my vote.

01:15:45.410 --> 01:15:46.542
I’m way too obvious.

01:15:46.716 --> 01:15:49.109
So obvious
it’s not obvious.

01:15:49.283 --> 01:15:50.807
What is that smell?

01:15:51.590 --> 01:15:54.419
Oh, shit! Pizza’s in the oven.

01:15:57.030 --> 01:15:58.466
Bathroom break.

01:16:02.035 --> 01:16:05.343
We should not have left Tatum
alone with Gen-Z Billy Loomis.

01:16:05.517 --> 01:16:06.910
Okay? I’m not feeling good
about that.

01:16:07.084 --> 01:16:09.390
Do you find it weird
that two very real suspects

01:16:09.565 --> 01:16:10.783
just conveniently disappeared?

01:16:12.002 --> 01:16:13.220
I really don’t want
to get stabbed tonight.

01:16:13.394 --> 01:16:14.961
Let’s go find Tatum.

01:16:16.615 --> 01:16:17.964
Okay.

01:16:21.881 --> 01:16:23.970
It’s locked.
We are locked in.

01:16:24.144 --> 01:16:26.799
[sighs] There must be
another way out of here.

01:16:26.973 --> 01:16:28.061
Let’s try
the dining room.

01:16:29.628 --> 01:16:31.630
[lights buzzing]

01:16:43.468 --> 01:16:45.426
Oven’s a piece of shit.

01:16:46.993 --> 01:16:49.256
[sighs]
[clattering]

01:17:05.838 --> 01:17:07.318
[gasps]

01:17:14.934 --> 01:17:15.892
Fuck.

01:17:18.372 --> 01:17:19.635
[breathing heavily]

01:17:23.769 --> 01:17:26.206
Where’s the fucking door?

01:17:31.298 --> 01:17:32.778
Hey. The kitchen.

01:17:32.952 --> 01:17:34.998
There has to be a back door.

01:17:35.172 --> 01:17:36.173
[clattering]

01:17:38.654 --> 01:17:39.872
That’s not good.

01:17:48.751 --> 01:17:50.404
[gasps, groans]

01:17:54.408 --> 01:17:56.106
[shouts, grunts]

01:18:03.809 --> 01:18:05.855
[screams, grunts]

01:18:11.469 --> 01:18:13.123
[grunts][groans]

01:18:16.387 --> 01:18:17.431
Aw, shit.

01:18:18.476 --> 01:18:19.695
[Mindy] Hey, cupcake!

01:18:21.348 --> 01:18:23.089
[groans]

01:18:30.836 --> 01:18:32.272
Hey, hey, hey.
Whoa, whoa, whoa.

01:18:32.446 --> 01:18:34.144
The killer is in there.
Hey, hey. I got this.

01:18:34.318 --> 01:18:36.407
Don’t go in there.
It’s okay, I got this.

01:18:36.581 --> 01:18:38.714
I got this, I got this!

01:18:40.193 --> 01:18:41.238
Lucas!

01:18:54.077 --> 01:18:55.774
[Lucas coughs]
[Chloe] Oh, my God.

01:18:56.775 --> 01:18:57.994
Oh, God.

01:19:03.042 --> 01:19:05.044
[keys jingling]

01:19:05.828 --> 01:19:06.611
[clattering]

01:19:06.785 --> 01:19:07.873
[gasps]

01:19:14.227 --> 01:19:15.315
Fuck.

01:19:22.366 --> 01:19:23.759
[footsteps thudding]

01:19:30.374 --> 01:19:31.897
[footsteps stop]

01:19:51.438 --> 01:19:53.353
[breathing shakily]

01:19:53.527 --> 01:19:55.138
[Lucas grunting]

01:19:55.312 --> 01:19:57.183
[door opens]

01:20:06.758 --> 01:20:07.803
[Chloe] Lucas.

01:20:08.978 --> 01:20:10.022
[screams]

01:20:24.428 --> 01:20:26.038
[choking, gurgling]

01:20:36.527 --> 01:20:38.834
[gasps, groans]

01:20:50.062 --> 01:20:51.237
No.

01:20:59.071 --> 01:21:01.987
No. Help. No.

01:21:02.161 --> 01:21:05.556
No, no, no. No! [coughs]

01:21:28.100 --> 01:21:29.493
[groans]

01:21:38.894 --> 01:21:40.939
[gurgling]

01:21:52.385 --> 01:21:53.909
[crickets chirping]

01:21:55.127 --> 01:21:56.650
[dog barking]
[Tatum breathing heavily]

01:22:10.229 --> 01:22:11.143
No!

01:22:11.317 --> 01:22:13.537
[ominous music plays]

01:22:15.974 --> 01:22:17.584
Open up, please! Please!

01:22:17.758 --> 01:22:19.195
Come on! [grunts]

01:22:25.549 --> 01:22:27.246
[suspenseful music plays]

01:22:28.552 --> 01:22:29.945
[footsteps approaching]

01:22:31.294 --> 01:22:32.599
[shouts, grunts]

01:22:37.039 --> 01:22:39.215
Help! Please,
somebody help me!

01:22:39.389 --> 01:22:42.609
He’s trying to kill me!
Please!

01:22:42.783 --> 01:22:45.917
Someone help me! [shrieks]

01:22:49.268 --> 01:22:50.835
[screams]

01:22:55.927 --> 01:22:57.015
[grunting]

01:23:04.544 --> 01:23:06.111
[music stops]

01:23:17.122 --> 01:23:19.124
[breathing heavily]

01:23:20.691 --> 01:23:21.997
[ominous music plays]

01:23:39.405 --> 01:23:41.233
[screams]
I found you.

01:23:41.407 --> 01:23:43.192
Did you see him? The killer?

01:23:43.366 --> 01:23:46.325
No, I didn’t see anyone.
You hit me.
Got me real good, too.

01:23:46.499 --> 01:23:47.761
We have to get out of here.

01:23:47.935 --> 01:23:49.328
Tate, listen.

01:23:49.502 --> 01:23:50.677
It’s not me, Tate.

01:23:50.851 --> 01:23:53.767
I know. I know, I’m sorry.

01:23:54.768 --> 01:23:56.944
I would never hurt you, okay?

01:24:03.864 --> 01:24:05.083
No!

01:24:05.257 --> 01:24:06.563
[alarm blaring]

01:24:16.834 --> 01:24:18.096
Help!

01:24:34.504 --> 01:24:35.853
[door buzzes]

01:24:45.863 --> 01:24:47.778
[Sidney breathing heavily]

01:25:02.749 --> 01:25:04.099
[rattling]

01:25:22.900 --> 01:25:24.380
[phone rings]

01:25:42.311 --> 01:25:45.662
[tense music playing]

01:25:50.101 --> 01:25:51.363
Oh, God.

01:25:52.103 --> 01:25:53.626
[breathes heavily]

01:26:10.339 --> 01:26:11.601
[knocking on door]

01:26:17.215 --> 01:26:18.564
[keypad beeping]

01:26:20.044 --> 01:26:21.698
[door buzzes]

01:26:28.705 --> 01:26:30.576
[grunting]

01:26:47.332 --> 01:26:48.333
[Sidney] Oh, God.

01:26:52.207 --> 01:26:53.425
[screams]

01:26:55.862 --> 01:26:58.343
[Sidney on phone] Tatum.
Mom!

01:26:58.517 --> 01:27:00.040
I’m coming, okay?

01:27:00.215 --> 01:27:01.955
[Tatum, distorted dialogue]
He’s at the door!

01:27:02.129 --> 01:27:05.742
Oh, shit. Oh, shit.
[Tatum crying, distorted]

01:27:06.438 --> 01:27:08.658
Oh, fuck you, phone.

01:27:08.832 --> 01:27:10.486
[Tatum] I can’t hear you!
I can’t hear you!

01:27:10.660 --> 01:27:13.140
Okay. Okay.

01:27:14.011 --> 01:27:15.186
Tatum, listen to me.

01:27:15.360 --> 01:27:16.666
I’m not gonna make it in time.

01:27:16.840 --> 01:27:18.711
But I’m gonna stay with you.

01:27:18.885 --> 01:27:21.192
You need to get the gun.
It’s in the safe.

01:27:21.366 --> 01:27:22.933
[pounding on door]

01:27:23.107 --> 01:27:24.369
Okay.

01:27:24.543 --> 01:27:26.110
The code is your birthday.

01:27:36.207 --> 01:27:38.165
[stammering] I don’t know
how to use this.

01:27:38.340 --> 01:27:41.125
I’m gonna talk you through it.
You have your earbuds?

01:27:41.299 --> 01:27:43.562
Well, put them in, okay?
You’re gonna need both hands.

01:27:43.736 --> 01:27:44.737
[Tatum] Okay.

01:27:47.610 --> 01:27:50.221
[pounding]

01:27:52.745 --> 01:27:54.399
Okay. Okay.
[pounding stops]

01:27:56.488 --> 01:27:57.489
Wait.

01:27:58.925 --> 01:28:00.927
I don’t hear him.
I think he left.

01:28:02.799 --> 01:28:04.670
No, he’s trying to find
another way in.

01:28:04.844 --> 01:28:06.846
[pounding resumes]
Oh, Mom, hurry!

01:28:07.020 --> 01:28:09.284
Okay, baby, listen to me.

01:28:09.458 --> 01:28:12.330
[stammering] The gun is--
It’s loaded,

01:28:12.504 --> 01:28:15.333
so you have to turn
the safety off, all right?

01:28:15.507 --> 01:28:17.117
You see that little switch?

01:28:17.901 --> 01:28:19.990
Flip it up. There’s a red dot.

01:28:20.164 --> 01:28:21.513
[gun clicks]
I see it.

01:28:21.687 --> 01:28:25.082
Okay. So all you have to
do now is you point

01:28:25.256 --> 01:28:28.694
and you pull the trigger.
You aim for center mass, okay?

01:28:28.868 --> 01:28:30.740
And when he goes down,
you shoot him in the head.

01:28:33.003 --> 01:28:35.440
[sobbing] I can’t.

01:28:36.441 --> 01:28:39.357
I’m not like you. I can’t.

01:28:39.531 --> 01:28:40.880
Tatum, you are.

01:28:41.054 --> 01:28:42.621
You are like me.

01:28:42.795 --> 01:28:44.362
I saw your interview.

01:28:45.363 --> 01:28:46.408
Baby, focus.

01:28:46.582 --> 01:28:48.540
We’re gonna do this together.

01:28:48.714 --> 01:28:50.760
[sobbing]

01:28:50.934 --> 01:28:52.414
He killed Ben.

01:28:53.806 --> 01:28:55.808
He killed him.

01:28:56.940 --> 01:29:00.073
Right now
you need to survive. Okay?

01:29:00.247 --> 01:29:02.337
That is what’s important
right now.

01:29:05.862 --> 01:29:07.951
[shattering]

01:29:08.952 --> 01:29:10.388
[Sidney] Okay.

01:29:10.562 --> 01:29:12.608
You’re gonna have to shoot him
through the wall.

01:29:13.260 --> 01:29:14.305
[Tatum] Where?

01:29:15.654 --> 01:29:17.352
[Sidney] Okay, you’re gonna
shoot the calendar.

01:29:17.526 --> 01:29:19.136
Fire through the calendar.
No, wait.

01:29:19.310 --> 01:29:20.442
Wait. He’s moving.

01:29:20.616 --> 01:29:21.617
Mom?

01:29:22.357 --> 01:29:23.183
To the right of the door.

01:29:23.358 --> 01:29:24.837
Shoot him now! Do it now!

01:29:25.011 --> 01:29:26.143
[screams]

01:29:30.103 --> 01:29:31.104
Oh, you got him.

01:29:31.278 --> 01:29:33.498
[breathing heavily]

01:29:36.196 --> 01:29:37.720
You got him.

01:29:37.894 --> 01:29:39.156
Okay.

01:30:00.046 --> 01:30:01.700
Okay, listen, you’re gonna
have to walk around him.

01:30:01.874 --> 01:30:03.789
But before you do that,
you shoot him in the head.

01:30:05.051 --> 01:30:07.576
But he’s dead, I got him.

01:30:07.750 --> 01:30:09.491
[Sidney] I know, baby.
You need to make sure.

01:30:09.665 --> 01:30:12.319
You shoot him. You shoot him
in the head right now.

01:30:13.016 --> 01:30:14.278
[Tatum screams]

01:30:14.887 --> 01:30:16.715
Tatum... Tatum!

01:30:19.152 --> 01:30:20.023
Tatum!

01:30:20.197 --> 01:30:21.764
Mom! Mom!

01:30:35.865 --> 01:30:37.867
[grunts]

01:30:59.584 --> 01:31:00.629
[Tatum gasps]

01:31:00.803 --> 01:31:03.327
[menacing music playing]

01:31:08.071 --> 01:31:11.030
[screaming]

01:31:13.076 --> 01:31:13.946
[footsteps approaching]

01:31:14.120 --> 01:31:15.774
Tatum!

01:31:20.997 --> 01:31:23.521
[phone ringing]

01:31:23.695 --> 01:31:27.264
[caller] Hello, Sidney.
Are we having fun yet?

01:31:27.438 --> 01:31:28.787
If you hurt her...

01:31:28.961 --> 01:31:31.573
Relax.
I’m not going to hurt her

01:31:31.747 --> 01:31:33.705
until you’re here
to see it.

01:31:33.879 --> 01:31:36.621
Where are you?
Where the heart is...

01:31:36.795 --> 01:31:39.537
until I stab a knife
through it.

01:31:39.711 --> 01:31:41.278
Come alone.

01:31:57.207 --> 01:31:58.513
[breathes shakily]

01:32:33.939 --> 01:32:35.854
[Ghostface]
Welcome home, Sidney.

01:32:36.028 --> 01:32:37.987
We’ve been waiting for you.

01:32:38.161 --> 01:32:39.684
[Stu, distorted]
Waiting for you.

01:32:40.467 --> 01:32:41.947
Thanks for coming alone.

01:32:42.121 --> 01:32:44.950
It makes it so much easier
that you followed the rules.

01:32:45.124 --> 01:32:46.473
Stop this shit.

01:32:46.648 --> 01:32:48.258
If you’re Stu, show yourself!
[Stu chuckles]

01:32:49.738 --> 01:32:51.435
Where am I?

01:32:55.047 --> 01:32:56.527
Can you find me?

01:32:58.050 --> 01:32:59.443
It’s not really me.

01:33:00.662 --> 01:33:02.402
You want to know
who I really am?

01:33:06.058 --> 01:33:07.407
Remember me?

01:33:08.626 --> 01:33:11.020
I’ll never forgive you for
what you did to my son.

01:33:11.194 --> 01:33:13.544
And you know what?
I would do it again and again.

01:33:13.718 --> 01:33:16.068
Your mother destroyed my life.

01:33:16.242 --> 01:33:17.635
But let’s face it.

01:33:17.809 --> 01:33:19.637
She destroyed you, too.

01:33:21.683 --> 01:33:24.337
In the same way that you’ve
destroyed your own daughter.

01:33:24.511 --> 01:33:26.296
Fuck whoever you are!

01:33:26.470 --> 01:33:27.819
[chuckling]

01:33:27.993 --> 01:33:29.734
Over here!

01:33:29.908 --> 01:33:31.388
It’s me, sis.

01:33:32.911 --> 01:33:34.521
Do you want to make a movie?

01:33:34.696 --> 01:33:38.177
Oh. How about a scary one?

01:33:38.351 --> 01:33:40.353
I’ve been working on
this great script.

01:33:42.051 --> 01:33:43.008
Come on, Sid.

01:33:43.661 --> 01:33:45.402
We’re family.

01:33:45.576 --> 01:33:48.405
It really comes down to
family, doesn’t it, Sid?

01:33:50.146 --> 01:33:53.584
I mean, we both know how far
we’d go for our own family.

01:33:54.846 --> 01:33:56.892
And friends, of course.

01:33:58.284 --> 01:34:00.939
But all your friends die for
just being near you.

01:34:01.810 --> 01:34:03.681
I died for you, Sidney.

01:34:05.335 --> 01:34:06.858
Doesn’t that
mean anything to you?

01:34:07.032 --> 01:34:09.252
Where is my daughter?

01:34:10.427 --> 01:34:12.168
I thought I’d go back to
where it all started.

01:34:12.342 --> 01:34:14.605
A phone call, a girl,

01:34:14.779 --> 01:34:16.128
and someone she cares about

01:34:16.302 --> 01:34:19.001
tied to a chair
outside of her house.

01:34:24.659 --> 01:34:25.921
[groans]

01:34:26.095 --> 01:34:27.574
Okay. Okay.

01:34:29.315 --> 01:34:30.360
Okay.

01:34:36.105 --> 01:34:37.628
Tatum, baby, I’m sorry.

01:34:38.498 --> 01:34:39.543
Just...

01:34:41.240 --> 01:34:43.025
What do you want from me?
Please tell me.

01:34:46.158 --> 01:34:47.682
[groans, sniffles]

01:34:50.467 --> 01:34:51.381
You.

01:34:51.555 --> 01:34:54.210
Yeah. Me.

01:34:54.384 --> 01:34:57.126
Well, me and Karl.

01:34:57.300 --> 01:34:58.780
[Sidney] Karl is dead.
Mm-hmm.

01:35:00.085 --> 01:35:01.391
And I would be, too,

01:35:02.566 --> 01:35:04.699
but your daughter
missed my head.

01:35:06.004 --> 01:35:09.225
You’ve always got to
shoot them in the head.

01:35:09.399 --> 01:35:10.661
Okay, okay.

01:35:11.836 --> 01:35:13.185
Isn’t that right,

01:35:14.056 --> 01:35:15.057
Stu?

01:35:16.493 --> 01:35:18.234
[Sidney breathes heavily]

01:35:23.282 --> 01:35:24.501
[whimpering]

01:35:24.675 --> 01:35:26.024
Okay, okay.

01:35:31.638 --> 01:35:32.901
[whispers]
I’ll be right back.

01:35:38.471 --> 01:35:39.516
[grunts]

01:35:41.823 --> 01:35:43.041
[groaning]

01:35:44.173 --> 01:35:45.348
[grunts, pants]

01:35:46.218 --> 01:35:47.698
[Tatum whimpering]
Mark.

01:35:47.872 --> 01:35:48.873
Ah-ah-ah-ah.

01:35:49.047 --> 01:35:50.048
Okay.

01:35:50.222 --> 01:35:51.310
[groans]

01:35:52.703 --> 01:35:54.487
[groans]
[Marco chuckles]

01:35:55.445 --> 01:35:56.489
Look at that!

01:35:56.663 --> 01:35:58.448
He’s still alive.

01:35:59.362 --> 01:36:00.537
That is a tough motherfucker.

01:36:00.711 --> 01:36:01.756
Fuck you!

01:36:07.936 --> 01:36:09.938
Jessica. What?

01:36:10.112 --> 01:36:11.287
Hi, neighbor.

01:36:12.201 --> 01:36:13.463
How you holding up?

01:36:14.290 --> 01:36:15.291
[Marco chuckles]

01:36:16.248 --> 01:36:18.250
You didn’t really think
it was Stu?

01:36:19.774 --> 01:36:21.993
Because that’d be dumb.
Stu’s dead.

01:36:22.951 --> 01:36:24.604
You know,
alive in spirit, but...

01:36:25.736 --> 01:36:26.911
dead.

01:36:27.085 --> 01:36:29.261
See,
I have a background in A.I.

01:36:29.435 --> 01:36:32.874
I was a Google security
specialist once upon a time.
Before Fallbrook.

01:36:33.048 --> 01:36:35.006
Bringing Stu back was my idea.

01:36:35.180 --> 01:36:36.921
No, no, no, no,
it was my idea.

01:36:37.095 --> 01:36:39.358
No, I just let you think
it was your idea.

01:36:39.532 --> 01:36:41.012
Jessica, please,
what are you doing?

01:36:41.186 --> 01:36:44.015
"Oh, Jessica." "Oh, please."
"Oh, what are you doing?"

01:36:44.189 --> 01:36:47.889
God, I don’t recognize you.
I mean, what happened to you?

01:36:48.977 --> 01:36:50.674
You know, you’ve really
let me down, Sid.

01:36:50.848 --> 01:36:53.720
Listen to me. This isn’t you.

01:36:53.895 --> 01:36:55.897
Whatever this is,
there’s another way.

01:36:56.071 --> 01:36:57.246
Oh, I know.

01:36:57.420 --> 01:36:59.117
There’s always another way.

01:36:59.291 --> 01:37:01.337
[chuckles, grunts]
Excuse me.

01:37:01.511 --> 01:37:04.296
You taught me that.
It’s in your book.

01:37:06.211 --> 01:37:07.822
You saved my life, Sidney.

01:37:09.258 --> 01:37:10.520
Before you ruined it.

01:37:12.087 --> 01:37:14.002
You know about
my abusive marriage, right?

01:37:15.351 --> 01:37:17.483
I was really trapped,
and I couldn’t see a way out.

01:37:17.657 --> 01:37:22.010
But then I read
Out of Darkness
by Sidney Prescott.

01:37:22.184 --> 01:37:24.099
Oh, it’s such a great book!

01:37:24.273 --> 01:37:28.494
And then I realized that
your life, it comes down to
one simple truth.

01:37:30.670 --> 01:37:32.672
Sidney Prescott kills
the bad guy.

01:37:34.457 --> 01:37:35.806
That’s your purpose.

01:37:36.981 --> 01:37:39.941
You are a real-life
scream queen.

01:37:40.811 --> 01:37:42.334
The final girl.

01:37:43.727 --> 01:37:45.772
God, you inspire me!

01:37:47.165 --> 01:37:50.603
So I started planning
and doing Pilates,

01:37:50.777 --> 01:37:53.606
and then I pulled a Sidney

01:37:53.780 --> 01:37:55.391
and I killed my husband!

01:37:55.565 --> 01:37:57.001
[both chuckling]

01:37:57.175 --> 01:37:59.134
[Jessica]
I got away with it, too.

01:38:00.613 --> 01:38:03.747
And I had you to thank for it.
[chuckling]

01:38:03.921 --> 01:38:05.488
But then you went away, Sid!

01:38:05.662 --> 01:38:07.577
And you didn’t go to New York.

01:38:07.751 --> 01:38:09.927
A Ghostface attack
doesn’t count
if you’re not there.

01:38:10.101 --> 01:38:11.015
You disappeared.

01:38:11.189 --> 01:38:12.582
Why, Sidney?

01:38:12.756 --> 01:38:15.106
I wanted people to see
there was life after trauma.

01:38:15.280 --> 01:38:16.716
But there isn’t for you!

01:38:18.109 --> 01:38:20.938
Trauma is your life.

01:38:21.983 --> 01:38:23.071
When you disappeared,

01:38:23.245 --> 01:38:25.290
do you know how much
that hurt me?

01:38:25.464 --> 01:38:28.032
I mean,
I couldn’t fucking handle it!

01:38:28.206 --> 01:38:29.816
I checked myself
into a facility.

01:38:29.991 --> 01:38:31.514
Fallbrook.
That’s where we met.

01:38:31.688 --> 01:38:33.995
Okay, I’m talking,
so don’t interrupt me, okay?

01:38:34.169 --> 01:38:36.345
Great. Fuck.
Where the fuck was I?

01:38:36.519 --> 01:38:38.173
Shit. Fuck!

01:38:38.347 --> 01:38:40.653
New York. Pilates.
You disappeared.

01:38:40.827 --> 01:38:43.091
Fallbrook.
Fallbrook. Fallbrook, yes!

01:38:43.265 --> 01:38:45.745
It was the closest psychiatric
center that I could find

01:38:45.920 --> 01:38:48.400
because I had to be near you.

01:38:50.141 --> 01:38:55.059
And that finally brings us
to tonight.

01:38:55.233 --> 01:38:57.888
[Sidney]
Okay, Jessica, you’re right,
I’ve been selfish.

01:38:58.062 --> 01:39:00.108
I can do better.
We can start over.

01:39:00.282 --> 01:39:01.936
I am starting over.

01:39:06.027 --> 01:39:07.202
By killing you.

01:39:08.899 --> 01:39:10.205
No more baggage.

01:39:11.423 --> 01:39:12.990
I am releasing it all.

01:39:14.252 --> 01:39:15.645
What about Lucas?
You have a son.

01:39:15.819 --> 01:39:18.126
Oh, no, no. He’s gone, Sid.

01:39:18.300 --> 01:39:20.389
I mean, he was too much
like his father.

01:39:20.998 --> 01:39:21.999
And now

01:39:23.435 --> 01:39:25.089
I can have a new beginning.

01:39:29.964 --> 01:39:32.270
Do you think that you’ve been
a good mother to Tatum?

01:39:33.837 --> 01:39:36.622
I mean, you really haven’t
taught her anything useful,
am I right?

01:39:36.796 --> 01:39:38.276
[scoffs]
[Jessica chuckles]

01:39:39.321 --> 01:39:41.540
You’ve kept the survivor
all to yourself.

01:39:41.714 --> 01:39:44.761
But that’s okay.
Because I’m gonna teach her!

01:39:48.373 --> 01:39:50.897
She’s gonna watch
her mother die.

01:39:51.072 --> 01:39:52.725
Just like you did.

01:39:54.205 --> 01:39:55.728
The cycle continues.

01:39:55.902 --> 01:39:57.165
No.

01:39:57.339 --> 01:39:58.905
[Jessica] You see,
it finally dawned on me.

01:40:00.037 --> 01:40:02.083
I don’t need you.

01:40:02.257 --> 01:40:04.389
I mean, none of us do.
Let’s face it,

01:40:04.563 --> 01:40:07.218
you’re kind of past your prime
for a final girl.

01:40:07.958 --> 01:40:10.395
I’m creating Sidney 2.0.

01:40:11.614 --> 01:40:13.181
Watch closely, Tatum.

01:40:21.363 --> 01:40:22.407
Okay.

01:40:23.626 --> 01:40:25.019
Okay, honey,

01:40:25.193 --> 01:40:26.368
you’re gonna need
to call an ambulance. Okay?

01:40:26.542 --> 01:40:27.630
What?

01:40:27.804 --> 01:40:29.240
Mom! No, wait!
Where are you going?

01:40:29.414 --> 01:40:30.328
Stay with your dad.

01:40:30.502 --> 01:40:32.417
No, no, no, no, Mom! God, no!

01:40:47.780 --> 01:40:48.781
[Jessica whispers] Sidney.

01:40:49.826 --> 01:40:52.263
Sidney...

01:40:52.437 --> 01:40:53.482
Please.

01:40:53.656 --> 01:40:55.005
[clattering]

01:40:55.179 --> 01:40:56.833
[boom box blares]
["Look Out For Me" playing]

01:41:10.325 --> 01:41:11.326
[music stops]

01:41:16.418 --> 01:41:17.593
[screams]

01:41:18.768 --> 01:41:19.812
[both grunting]

01:41:38.048 --> 01:41:39.789
Is that all you’ve got?
[screams]

01:41:43.184 --> 01:41:44.402
[screaming]

01:42:08.774 --> 01:42:09.819
Fuck!

01:42:30.056 --> 01:42:31.275
[Sidney panting, coughing]

01:42:31.449 --> 01:42:32.624
Are you okay?

01:42:33.886 --> 01:42:34.931
You got to shoot her
in the head.

01:42:35.105 --> 01:42:36.585
What?
Shoot her in the--

01:42:37.847 --> 01:42:38.674
Shit!

01:42:38.848 --> 01:42:41.024
Damn it. Okay.

01:42:45.724 --> 01:42:47.117
Come on.

01:42:51.904 --> 01:42:53.254
[screaming]

01:43:11.663 --> 01:43:12.795
You okay?

01:43:16.668 --> 01:43:19.105
I’m Sidney
fucking Prescott’s daughter.

01:43:27.549 --> 01:43:28.941
Past my prime.

01:43:30.421 --> 01:43:31.379
Fuck you.

01:43:41.563 --> 01:43:43.956
This is Robbie Rivers
with an exclusive

01:43:44.130 --> 01:43:45.741
on the scene, live report,

01:43:45.915 --> 01:43:47.830
at the home of
police chief Mark Evans,

01:43:48.004 --> 01:43:50.485
where a bloody nightmare
has come to an end.

01:43:58.101 --> 01:43:59.233
[pained grunt]

01:44:06.457 --> 01:44:07.980
Network wants a live remote.

01:44:08.154 --> 01:44:10.069
No way. Too much blood loss.

01:44:10.244 --> 01:44:11.767
I can’t hold a camera.

01:44:12.507 --> 01:44:13.812
I was hoping you’d do it.

01:44:13.986 --> 01:44:15.684
I do feel better.

01:44:15.858 --> 01:44:17.642
We’re gonna need to frame out
the blood, though.

01:44:17.816 --> 01:44:19.165
I’ll get the tripod.

01:44:42.406 --> 01:44:43.929
Thanks for ditching me.

01:44:45.496 --> 01:44:47.150
Seriously,
what was that about?

01:44:49.283 --> 01:44:52.068
You have always
had my back, Gale.

01:44:53.287 --> 01:44:54.549
I should have
gone to New York.

01:44:55.463 --> 01:44:56.638
I should have
been there for you.

01:44:56.812 --> 01:44:57.943
No, Sid.

01:44:58.117 --> 01:44:59.945
And I was wrong
about something.

01:45:00.859 --> 01:45:02.383
I do trust...

01:45:04.863 --> 01:45:06.125
I trust you.

01:45:16.222 --> 01:45:17.441
You want me to
drive you to the hospital?

01:45:17.615 --> 01:45:19.443
- I’d love that.
- Okay.

01:45:19.617 --> 01:45:20.618
Just give me a minute.

01:45:38.244 --> 01:45:40.551
This is exactly what
I didn’t want for you.

01:45:43.162 --> 01:45:44.816
I don’t think
it was up to you.

01:45:52.258 --> 01:45:53.869
Tatum was my best friend.

01:45:55.740 --> 01:45:57.438
She was funny,

01:45:58.613 --> 01:45:59.918
and outspoken.

01:46:00.832 --> 01:46:03.705
Said whatever was on her mind.

01:46:03.879 --> 01:46:05.097
No edit whatsoever.

01:46:07.099 --> 01:46:10.276
And she was strong.

01:46:10.799 --> 01:46:12.844
And fierce.

01:46:13.018 --> 01:46:16.370
She wasn’t afraid of anything.

01:46:20.199 --> 01:46:22.898
So that’s why
I named you Tatum.

01:46:23.942 --> 01:46:26.945
Because that was my wish

01:46:27.729 --> 01:46:28.730
for you.

01:46:30.688 --> 01:46:32.168
To be strong...

01:46:34.170 --> 01:46:35.650
and unafraid.

01:46:39.610 --> 01:46:41.046
What else can I tell you?

01:46:43.353 --> 01:46:44.659
That’s enough for now.

01:46:46.922 --> 01:46:47.966
Okay.

01:46:52.231 --> 01:46:55.017
You know I love you.
I love you more.

01:46:58.150 --> 01:47:00.109
Let’s go
see your dad.
Yeah.

01:47:32.924 --> 01:47:35.361
["Creepin" playing]

01:49:40.356 --> 01:49:42.924
Three, two...

01:49:43.098 --> 01:49:45.579
It all began
last Thursday night
in Woodsboro, California,

01:49:45.753 --> 01:49:48.190
at a house made infamous
for the stashing.

01:49:48.364 --> 01:49:51.454
Cut. I got caught between
"stabbing" and "slashing".

01:49:51.628 --> 01:49:52.586
Hey, you suck at this.

01:49:52.760 --> 01:49:53.848
Shut up. Go again.

01:49:54.022 --> 01:49:55.893
Copy that. Three, two...

01:49:56.938 --> 01:49:59.201
Hi. I’m Mindy Meeks-Mar--
I don’t know.

01:49:59.375 --> 01:50:01.682
[Chad chuckling] You messed up
your own name, dude?

01:50:01.856 --> 01:50:04.815
Stop laughing!

01:50:07.252 --> 01:50:09.951
Okay. Three, two...

01:50:11.169 --> 01:50:13.171
Hi. I’m Mindy Meeks-Martin,

01:50:13.345 --> 01:50:14.695
three-time Ghostface survivor

01:50:14.869 --> 01:50:16.784
and new reporter
for CBS 7, New York.

01:50:16.958 --> 01:50:19.787
[Chad] Oh, my God, I wasn’t
recording any of that.
One second.

01:50:19.961 --> 01:50:20.875
[Mindy] I hate you.

01:50:21.049 --> 01:50:22.790
["Twisting The Knife" playing]

01:53:42.163 --> 01:53:43.164
[music ends]
